WEBVTT

00:34.133 --> 00:36.036
[♪♪♪]

00:45.710 --> 00:48.479
<i>♪ We play for keeps
Uh-huh ♪</i>

00:48.481 --> 00:51.515
<i>♪ One wrong move
And we'll flood the streets ♪</i>

00:51.517 --> 00:55.052
[TIRES SQUEALING]

00:55.054 --> 00:56.821
<i>♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>

00:56.823 --> 00:59.390
<i>♪ Make no mistake
We play for keeps ♪</i>

00:59.392 --> 01:01.626
<i>♪ We play for keeps ♪</i>

01:01.628 --> 01:03.796
<i>♪ We play for keeps ♪</i>

01:08.600 --> 01:11.271
<i>♪ W-w-we play for keeps ♪</i>

01:17.575 --> 01:19.311
<i>♪ We play for keeps ♪</i>

01:21.746 --> 01:24.481
Okay, is there a reason
you're trying to kill me?

01:24.483 --> 01:26.416
Yeah, I had to get you here
by 8 p.m.

01:26.418 --> 01:28.822
Annie's throwing
a surprise party for you.

01:30.022 --> 01:31.955
[SIGHS]

01:31.957 --> 01:34.624
Will you please try to act
surprised when you walk in?

01:34.626 --> 01:37.561
Yeah, yeah, I got you.
I got you, man.

01:37.563 --> 01:39.062
You think he'll be surprised?

01:39.064 --> 01:40.865
I'm so excited.
It's gonna be great.

01:40.867 --> 01:44.100
- Don't forget, surprised.
- Yeah, yeah.

01:44.102 --> 01:46.068
Oh, oh, oh, look, look.

01:46.070 --> 01:47.538
- You look great.
- ALL: Surprise!

01:47.540 --> 01:49.472
Oh, shit!

01:49.474 --> 01:51.041
It was all Annie.

01:51.043 --> 01:53.076
- MAN: We got you!
- SCOTT: What's up?

01:53.078 --> 01:54.613
Good to see you.
Come here.

01:56.248 --> 01:57.882
Mm!

01:57.884 --> 01:59.451
- Come here.
- What is...? What?

02:01.921 --> 02:03.654
I'm so proud of you.

02:03.656 --> 02:05.455
I don't know how you did this

02:05.457 --> 02:08.191
because I just closed the deal
like an hour ago.

02:08.193 --> 02:10.793
Yeah, that's the thing.
I had this planned for weeks.

02:10.794 --> 02:13.465
Because I knew
you were gonna close the deal.

02:14.834 --> 02:16.733
[SIGHS]
You're, uh...

02:16.735 --> 02:19.235
You really are something
special. You know that?

02:19.237 --> 02:20.939
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

02:23.109 --> 02:25.643
I need to borrow him
for one second, okay?

02:25.645 --> 02:27.143
Hey, everybody,
grab your glass

02:27.145 --> 02:28.714
because I'm about
to make a toast.

02:29.981 --> 02:31.548
To my best friend,

02:31.550 --> 02:34.317
and now the number-one earner
at the company,

02:34.319 --> 02:35.818
Scott Howard!

02:35.820 --> 02:37.989
[ALL CHEER]

02:37.991 --> 02:39.589
- Wait, you need this.
- Thank you.

02:39.591 --> 02:42.659
Appreciate you. Thank you, guys,
so much for coming.

02:42.661 --> 02:44.328
This is not just
a victory for me.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.262
This is a victory for all of us,
right?

02:46.264 --> 02:47.498
And to my wife,

02:47.500 --> 02:49.399
I love you,
I love you, I love you.

02:49.401 --> 02:50.536
- Thank you.
- I love you too.

02:51.804 --> 02:53.070
Yeah, bud!

02:53.072 --> 02:54.637
[ALL CHEER]

02:54.639 --> 02:56.542
[R&B MUSIC PLAYING SOFTLY]

03:01.781 --> 03:05.115
You remember
that conversation we had

03:05.117 --> 03:08.250
about buying that house
up in Napa?

03:08.252 --> 03:09.154
Yeah.

03:10.622 --> 03:12.524
You sure that's
something you want to do?

03:14.760 --> 03:15.894
I'm positive.

03:17.062 --> 03:18.298
I want that house.

03:19.664 --> 03:22.132
I want a family.

03:22.134 --> 03:25.068
I want our kids
to be able to play outside.

03:25.070 --> 03:26.072
[CHUCKLES]

03:27.073 --> 03:28.338
Could be nice.

03:28.340 --> 03:29.607
[SIRENS WAILING]

03:29.609 --> 03:31.841
Get away from
all of this noise.

03:31.843 --> 03:34.578
- Yeah.
- [CHUCKLES]

03:34.580 --> 03:38.482
SCOTT: <i>So this house has been
on the market for a while.</i>

03:38.484 --> 03:40.885
<i>Let's just not
get our hopes up, okay?</i>

03:40.887 --> 03:43.053
ANNIE: <i>I know, I know.
I'm just excited</i>

03:43.055 --> 03:44.887
<i>that we're finally
going to see it!</i>

03:44.889 --> 03:46.957
[♪♪♪]

03:46.959 --> 03:49.826
This is it. 6741 Arbor Road.

03:49.828 --> 03:53.162
<i>♪ Want to sing, so I just
La-dee-da-dee... ♪</i>

03:53.164 --> 03:56.534
Hope there's a house
at the end of this road.

03:56.536 --> 03:58.969
ANNIE:
Wow, this is so beautiful.

03:58.971 --> 04:01.739
<i>♪ I'm feeling so easy
And free... ♪</i>

04:01.741 --> 04:04.274
SCOTT:
And here we are.

04:04.276 --> 04:05.878
Wow.

04:10.081 --> 04:11.918
Doesn't look like
anyone's home.

04:13.218 --> 04:15.120
[LAWN MOWER HUMMING]

04:16.487 --> 04:18.223
No, I hear someone
in the back.

04:21.194 --> 04:22.095
Come on.

04:25.129 --> 04:27.531
SCOTT: Something tells me
Domino's won't deliver.

04:27.533 --> 04:28.434
[ANNIE CHUCKLES]

04:29.901 --> 04:31.735
ANNIE:
This is so pretty.

04:31.737 --> 04:32.838
SCOTT:
Watch your step.

04:35.507 --> 04:36.575
ANNIE:
Oh, honey, look.

04:38.610 --> 04:40.944
[INHALES SHARPLY]
I don't know.

04:40.946 --> 04:42.448
This might be the one.

04:44.350 --> 04:45.748
This is incredible.

04:45.750 --> 04:46.851
[GUNSHOT]

04:46.853 --> 04:48.452
- [BIRD CAWS]
- [RELOADS]

04:48.454 --> 04:49.952
[♪♪♪]

04:49.954 --> 04:51.257
[GUNSHOT]

04:52.958 --> 04:54.390
- We need to go.
- Here he comes.

04:54.392 --> 04:55.925
- MAN: Wait, wait.
- We need to go.

04:55.927 --> 04:57.127
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

04:57.129 --> 04:58.461
I didn't mean
to scare you.

04:58.463 --> 04:59.762
We have a bounty on deer.

04:59.764 --> 05:01.430
They're eating up
all the gardens.

05:01.432 --> 05:03.033
Go through them
in nothing flat.

05:03.035 --> 05:04.634
But there's an upside.

05:04.636 --> 05:06.036
You like venison?

05:06.038 --> 05:07.236
I-I don't know.

05:07.238 --> 05:09.272
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

05:09.274 --> 05:10.343
I'm Charlie Peck.

05:11.442 --> 05:13.644
Welcome to Foxglove.

05:13.646 --> 05:15.144
Scott Howard.

05:15.146 --> 05:17.313
This is my wife, Annie.

05:17.315 --> 05:19.284
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- Hi.

05:20.752 --> 05:22.952
I guess you want
to see the house, huh?

05:22.954 --> 05:24.454
- Yes. Yeah.
- Come on up.

05:24.456 --> 05:27.324
[LAUGHING]
Sorry. Sorry about that.

05:27.326 --> 05:29.796
We're gonna be laughing
about this soon. Come on.

05:32.363 --> 05:35.298
- [CHUCKLES] Yeah.
- You're gonna love my house.

05:35.300 --> 05:37.666
It might need a freshen-up,
but, uh...

05:37.668 --> 05:39.536
I think
you're gonna have to agree,

05:39.538 --> 05:40.840
it's got great bones.

05:42.307 --> 05:43.509
You guys got kids?

05:44.343 --> 05:45.843
Uh... Not yet.

05:45.845 --> 05:48.911
We raised two kids
in this house, my wife and I.

05:48.913 --> 05:49.815
Ellen.

05:51.216 --> 05:52.718
She's gone now.

05:53.951 --> 05:57.320
I lost her to cancer
two years ago.

05:57.322 --> 05:58.657
I'm sorry to hear that.

06:00.225 --> 06:02.192
So, what do you do, Scott?

06:02.194 --> 06:04.928
SCOTT: I'm a creative director
at Saunders and Ruddick

06:04.930 --> 06:06.329
in San Francisco.

06:06.331 --> 06:08.365
It's a branding
and advertising agency.

06:08.367 --> 06:10.000
CHARLIE:
Annie, do you work?

06:10.002 --> 06:12.469
ANNIE: I mostly write
for women's magazines.

06:12.471 --> 06:14.872
Articles about injustice,
women empowerment,

06:14.874 --> 06:16.973
self-love, that sort of thing.

06:16.975 --> 06:19.543
This view is beautiful.

06:19.545 --> 06:23.146
CHARLIE: My great-great-grandfather
built this house in 1905.

06:23.148 --> 06:24.882
It's the only house
I ever lived in.

06:24.884 --> 06:26.582
Why do you call it
Foxglove?

06:26.584 --> 06:29.985
The entire valley used
to be covered with the stuff.

06:29.987 --> 06:31.255
Now it's kind of rare.

06:31.257 --> 06:33.793
Foxglove is poisonous,
isn't it?

06:34.927 --> 06:36.325
Highly.

06:36.327 --> 06:39.361
Come on, I'm gonna give you
the grand tour.

06:39.363 --> 06:42.933
The house, it backs up
to a wooded nature preserve.

06:42.935 --> 06:44.567
SCOTT:
Lots of privacy, huh?

06:44.569 --> 06:48.238
- Nobody can build behind us.
- I love this marble.

06:48.240 --> 06:49.707
CHARLIE:
Do you cook, Annie?

06:49.709 --> 06:51.507
SCOTT:
She's a damn good cook.

06:51.509 --> 06:54.411
And a great baker.
And even better wife.

06:54.413 --> 06:55.646
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

06:55.648 --> 06:57.247
My grandmother
taught me to cook.

06:57.249 --> 06:58.983
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:58.985 --> 07:01.450
- That's a beautiful stone.
- Thank you.

07:01.452 --> 07:03.420
- Is that an emerald?
- It is.

07:03.422 --> 07:05.454
- Birthstone? No.
- Yeah.

07:05.456 --> 07:06.923
- ANNIE: Yeah.
- CHARLIE: So am I.

07:06.925 --> 07:08.224
- ANNIE: No way. Really?
- CHARLIE: Yeah.

07:08.226 --> 07:10.726
We're not gonna get
into how many years.

07:10.728 --> 07:11.829
That is crazy.

07:11.831 --> 07:12.863
Yep.

07:12.865 --> 07:14.865
Wow, that's a good sign.

07:14.867 --> 07:16.733
That's a good sign.

07:16.735 --> 07:20.704
So here's where I rule,
Scott.

07:20.706 --> 07:23.507
And I watch a lot of sports
in here and read.

07:23.509 --> 07:25.745
Hey, football's on.
You got a team?

07:27.012 --> 07:28.945
Yeah, yeah. Raiders.

07:28.947 --> 07:31.081
- Rams here.
- That's unfortunate.

07:31.083 --> 07:33.050
- You watch on that?
- Yeah.

07:33.052 --> 07:34.918
You got a big flat-screen,
right?

07:34.920 --> 07:37.654
- Yeah, a little something.
- We're basic cable around here,

07:37.656 --> 07:39.089
but you can put in
satellite.

07:39.091 --> 07:40.791
Okay.

07:40.793 --> 07:43.093
He's got more guns.

07:43.095 --> 07:45.896
- Nice-looking family.
- CHARLIE: Oh, why, thank you.

07:45.898 --> 07:48.231
After I sell the house,
Cassidy, my daughter,

07:48.233 --> 07:49.966
she wants me
to move down to Florida

07:49.968 --> 07:51.668
and live with them.

07:51.670 --> 07:54.103
Your wife
was really beautiful.

07:54.105 --> 07:56.072
Yeah.

07:56.074 --> 07:58.076
We always had a lot of love
in this house.

08:01.480 --> 08:04.012
[♪♪♪]

08:04.014 --> 08:05.916
[MOUTHS]
It's not that bad.

08:05.918 --> 08:08.250
- You want to see the upstairs?
- Yes.

08:08.252 --> 08:09.719
- Yes.
- Come on.

08:09.721 --> 08:10.889
Come on.

08:30.375 --> 08:32.006
Honey?

08:32.009 --> 08:34.645
Coming, coming.
Just looking at...

08:36.347 --> 08:37.716
all this old shit.

08:41.953 --> 08:43.552
Oh.

08:43.554 --> 08:44.821
A lot of yellow.

08:44.823 --> 08:47.589
This room hasn't been redone
in 20 years.

08:47.591 --> 08:49.658
So I figured
whoever buys the place

08:49.660 --> 08:51.196
will just make it their own.

08:53.865 --> 08:55.931
Beautiful terrace,
though.

08:55.933 --> 08:56.968
Yeah.

09:01.472 --> 09:02.539
- Hey.
- [GASPS]

09:02.541 --> 09:05.108
- You scared me.
- You okay?

09:05.110 --> 09:08.011
Night-blooming jasmine comes
through that terrace at night.

09:08.013 --> 09:09.415
Oh, it's just heaven.

09:12.850 --> 09:14.416
Oh, uh...

09:14.418 --> 09:15.954
Here's your linen closet.

09:17.355 --> 09:19.692
- Nice.
- Pretty much room for everything.

09:22.427 --> 09:25.027
This is a great kids' room.

09:25.029 --> 09:27.730
Originally,
this was the nursery.

09:27.732 --> 09:30.834
And then after the kids grew up
and left home,

09:30.836 --> 09:34.240
we turned it
into Ellen's sewing room.

09:38.177 --> 09:39.445
I'll give you a minute.

09:43.849 --> 09:45.448
I freaking love this.

09:45.450 --> 09:46.949
- Just be cool.
- I'm being cool.

09:46.951 --> 09:48.550
- I'm being totally cool.
- Okay.

09:48.552 --> 09:50.920
Take a breath.
Here we go. All right.

09:50.922 --> 09:53.857
CHARLIE: There's been a lot of
birthdays, cocktail parties,

09:53.859 --> 09:56.929
graduations, weddings,
Fourth of July out here.

09:58.230 --> 10:00.730
This is a special place,
isn't it?

10:00.732 --> 10:02.965
You see it, don't you, Annie?

10:02.967 --> 10:04.066
I'm gonna go...

10:04.068 --> 10:05.870
check out this pond.

10:07.272 --> 10:09.373
So, uh,
Charlie...

10:09.375 --> 10:12.541
How, uh...?
How motivated are you?

10:12.543 --> 10:14.511
CHARLIE:
If you want to know how much,

10:14.513 --> 10:16.816
the asking price is
3.5 million.

10:19.217 --> 10:20.684
If you can't afford it,

10:20.686 --> 10:22.888
you probably
shouldn't even be here.

10:24.155 --> 10:25.222
Annie.

10:25.224 --> 10:28.291
- Hm?
- We're leaving.

10:28.293 --> 10:29.593
ANNIE:
Oh.

10:29.595 --> 10:31.328
Thank you for showing us
your home.

10:31.330 --> 10:32.632
You bet.

10:33.798 --> 10:35.433
[MOUTHING WORDS]

10:41.173 --> 10:42.707
[SIGHS]

10:46.211 --> 10:47.810
What'd you think?

10:47.812 --> 10:49.447
Well, it's...

10:50.514 --> 10:51.449
Maybe not.

10:52.884 --> 10:54.151
Oh.

10:54.153 --> 10:55.451
[SIGHS]

10:55.453 --> 10:56.354
Listen.

10:57.423 --> 10:58.787
You have
to understand,

10:58.789 --> 11:01.123
I've had people salivating
to buy this house,

11:01.125 --> 11:04.396
but I'm very particular,
and I just like you two.

11:05.931 --> 11:09.733
I will throw in the furniture,
all the equipment,

11:09.735 --> 11:13.369
my tapestry,
and I'll knock off $200,000,

11:13.371 --> 11:16.440
and you can have it for 3.3.

11:16.442 --> 11:18.675
We still have a few more places
we got to see,

11:18.677 --> 11:20.877
but we'll let you know.

11:20.879 --> 11:23.479
I want you
to have this house.

11:23.481 --> 11:26.148
And I know
she wants this house.

11:26.150 --> 11:27.850
And you remember,

11:27.852 --> 11:31.121
if Mama ain't happy,
nobody's happy.

11:31.123 --> 11:33.489
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

11:33.491 --> 11:35.657
- Thanks for the advice.
- All right.

11:35.659 --> 11:37.694
And you look out
for the deer.

11:37.696 --> 11:39.095
- Okay.
- BOTH: Ha, ha.

11:39.097 --> 11:41.330
I told you, you'd be laughing
on the way home.

11:41.332 --> 11:44.133
- You... Yeah.
- Oh, man.

11:44.135 --> 11:47.270
- Did you just roll up the window on him?
- Yeah.

11:47.272 --> 11:49.608
Rolled up the window
on the Bambi killer.

11:52.009 --> 11:54.044
So, what'd you think
of the house?

11:54.046 --> 11:55.978
It's magical, right?

11:55.980 --> 11:58.180
SCOTT:
<i>Yeah, if old is magical.</i>

11:58.182 --> 11:59.518
ANNIE:
<i>Come on.</i>

12:00.586 --> 12:01.984
Foxglove.

12:01.986 --> 12:04.119
You really want this place,
don't you?

12:04.121 --> 12:05.354
I do.

12:05.356 --> 12:07.022
But you gotta want it too.

12:07.024 --> 12:08.424
SCOTT:
<i>It's an old house.</i>

12:08.426 --> 12:10.126
<i>It's gonna require
a lot of work.</i>

12:10.128 --> 12:11.695
<i>I don't do that kind of stuff.</i>

12:11.697 --> 12:13.530
ANNIE: <i>But I don't
mind a lot of work,</i>

12:13.532 --> 12:15.531
<i>and we could get someone
to help us.</i>

12:15.533 --> 12:18.667
<i>And to be honest, I
already have a thousand ideas.</i>

12:18.669 --> 12:20.905
I could see it in your eyes
the whole time.

12:23.875 --> 12:26.142
ANNIE:
<i>It'll be where our future is.</i>

12:26.144 --> 12:27.643
We get the house.

12:27.645 --> 12:29.412
We get the kids.

12:29.414 --> 12:30.882
We get the whole thing.

12:32.817 --> 12:34.385
SCOTT:
<i>What do I say to that, huh?</i>

12:35.254 --> 12:36.686
<i>[ANNIE CHUCKLES]</i>

12:36.688 --> 12:38.220
SCOTT:
<i>All right.</i>

12:38.222 --> 12:41.824
I'll talk to Marvin
and the partners tomorrow,

12:41.826 --> 12:43.095
see if I can swing it.

12:44.196 --> 12:45.297
Yes!

12:47.865 --> 12:49.802
<i>Do you think
we could move in next week?</i>

12:51.336 --> 12:53.302
ANNIE:
This to the kitchen.

12:53.304 --> 12:55.070
These are gonna go
in the bathroom.

12:55.072 --> 12:56.839
Yeah? Got it? Thank you.

12:56.841 --> 12:58.811
[TRUCK BEEPING]

13:00.544 --> 13:03.412
Okay, this is gonna go upstairs
in the master bedroom.

13:03.414 --> 13:06.182
And you know that little piece?

13:06.184 --> 13:08.153
We're gonna put that
in the other bedroom.

13:10.422 --> 13:12.421
[♪♪♪]

13:12.423 --> 13:14.994
<i>[CHILDREN LAUGHING]</i>

13:16.061 --> 13:17.629
[MACHINERY WHIRRING]

13:26.971 --> 13:28.470
It's all yours.

13:28.472 --> 13:30.440
[CHUCKLES]

13:30.442 --> 13:31.677
It's all ours now.

13:35.379 --> 13:36.282
Thank you.

13:37.816 --> 13:40.152
CHARLIE:
Well, this is the big handoff.

13:41.085 --> 13:42.288
Here's the keys...

13:43.455 --> 13:44.820
to all the doors and locks.

13:44.822 --> 13:47.025
I got it all marked,
color-coded.

13:48.259 --> 13:49.324
Thank you.

13:49.326 --> 13:51.294
Foxglove is yours now.

13:51.296 --> 13:52.829
We'll take good care of her.

13:52.831 --> 13:55.165
- I'm gonna hold you to that.
- I promise.

13:55.167 --> 13:56.465
Cross my heart.

13:56.467 --> 13:58.166
Aw...

13:58.168 --> 14:00.603
Ellen used to do that.

14:00.605 --> 14:01.639
Cross her heart.

14:03.542 --> 14:05.775
Listen, Charlie,
I know you have our e-mails.

14:05.777 --> 14:08.945
Keep in touch, we'd like to know
how you're doing. Right, Scott?

14:08.947 --> 14:11.680
SCOTT: Yeah, just let me call you back.
Okay, bye.

14:11.682 --> 14:13.449
Did I tell you
about the sprinklers?

14:13.451 --> 14:15.251
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yes, I did. I did.

14:15.253 --> 14:16.455
[CHUCKLES]

14:21.326 --> 14:22.228
You take care.

14:27.032 --> 14:28.198
Have a good,
uh...

14:28.200 --> 14:30.536
- Good time in Florida, buddy.
- Yep.

14:35.573 --> 14:38.140
- I feel bad for him.
- What?

14:38.142 --> 14:39.508
[CHARLIE HONKING]

14:39.510 --> 14:42.677
Don't feel bad for Charlie,
you know?

14:42.679 --> 14:44.647
Feel good for us.

14:44.649 --> 14:46.148
Okay.

14:46.150 --> 14:49.384
Make me some eggs, woman!
Make me some eggs.

14:49.386 --> 14:50.922
- Yes!
- [LAUGHING]

14:55.293 --> 14:56.629
- We did it.
- We did it.

14:57.696 --> 14:58.762
You happy?

14:58.764 --> 15:00.331
- I am.
- Good.

15:03.701 --> 15:05.271
Now the journey...

15:06.404 --> 15:08.405
can begin.

15:08.407 --> 15:10.209
Say goodbye to Charlie.

15:14.379 --> 15:15.380
Annie?

15:17.048 --> 15:18.147
Annie?

15:18.149 --> 15:19.350
Annie?

15:27.225 --> 15:28.724
This house
looks good on you.

15:28.726 --> 15:30.093
[CHUCKLES]

15:30.095 --> 15:31.261
You're so beautiful.

15:31.263 --> 15:32.598
[LAUGHS]

15:35.868 --> 15:36.936
Here's to us.

15:38.302 --> 15:40.002
And our new home.

15:40.004 --> 15:41.938
<i>♪ I like that you
Don't play fair ♪</i>

15:41.940 --> 15:45.108
<i>♪ Girl
Recipe for a disaster ♪</i>

15:45.110 --> 15:46.876
- <i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Girl ♪</i>

15:46.878 --> 15:49.545
<i>♪ When I'm just trying
To take my time ♪</i>

15:49.547 --> 15:51.113
<i>♪ Girl ♪</i>

15:51.115 --> 15:53.215
<i>♪ Stroke is getting deep
And faster ♪</i>

15:53.217 --> 15:55.017
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

15:55.019 --> 15:57.286
<i>♪ You're screaming
Like I'm out of line ♪</i>

15:57.288 --> 16:00.123
<i>♪ Who came to make
Sweet love? ♪</i>

16:00.125 --> 16:01.458
<i>♪ Not me ♪</i>

16:01.460 --> 16:02.925
<i>♪ Who came to kiss... ♪</i>

16:02.927 --> 16:04.560
[WHISPERS]
I love you.

16:04.562 --> 16:05.795
- <i>♪ Not me ♪</i>
- <i>♪ No ♪</i>

16:05.797 --> 16:08.431
<i>♪ Who came to beat it up? ♪</i>

16:08.433 --> 16:09.733
- <i>♪ Rocky ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

16:09.735 --> 16:11.400
<i>♪ And don't use those hands ♪</i>

16:11.402 --> 16:13.102
<i>♪ To put up that gate
And stop me ♪</i>

16:13.104 --> 16:15.438
- [PEOPLE LAUGHING]
- SCOTT: And there's the owner.

16:15.440 --> 16:17.406
He's just standing there,
staring at us.

16:17.408 --> 16:20.209
I mean, he comes towards us
with a rifle.

16:20.211 --> 16:22.011
- Bam!
- Oh, okay.

16:22.013 --> 16:24.848
- Shot a deer right behind us.
- ANNIE: Yeah.

16:24.850 --> 16:27.215
- Is this guy crazy?
- Man, he country.

16:27.217 --> 16:29.318
Then he said,
"You like venison?"

16:29.320 --> 16:31.787
- Not this fresh.
- [ALL LAUGHING]

16:31.789 --> 16:33.455
I don't want to see it
get killed.

16:33.457 --> 16:34.992
That's just the best way.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.928
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

16:40.999 --> 16:42.935
[URINATING]

16:45.636 --> 16:47.637
[RUSTLING]

16:47.639 --> 16:50.305
[FOOTSTEPS]

16:50.307 --> 16:52.211
[♪♪♪]

17:01.485 --> 17:02.388
Hello?

17:13.030 --> 17:14.963
Watch the deer
out here in the country.

17:14.964 --> 17:16.031
- Oh, yeah.
- Right.

17:16.034 --> 17:17.636
They better watch this ride.

17:24.342 --> 17:25.377
[SOFTLY]
What the hell?

17:26.545 --> 17:27.643
SCOTT:
What's up?

17:27.645 --> 17:29.412
[♪♪♪]

17:29.414 --> 17:32.014
There's a cigarette burn
on my car seat.

17:32.016 --> 17:34.049
Dude, you gotta stop smoking.
That's you.

17:34.051 --> 17:37.553
Me? This is my temple, Scott.
I would never smoke in here.

17:37.555 --> 17:39.122
Okay.

17:39.124 --> 17:40.526
Goddamn!

17:42.393 --> 17:43.692
Nice going, Mike.

17:43.694 --> 17:45.763
Rachel, please,
shut your magic lips.

17:47.164 --> 17:48.663
I didn't do it.

17:48.665 --> 17:50.333
- Did I say you did?
- Well, it made...

17:50.335 --> 17:51.903
You made it seem
like I did.

17:57.009 --> 17:59.909
Give them a year.
They'll be living next door.

17:59.911 --> 18:01.576
[ENGINE REVVING]

18:01.578 --> 18:02.578
I hope not.

18:02.580 --> 18:03.813
[LAUGHING]

18:03.815 --> 18:05.881
That's so shady.

18:05.883 --> 18:08.017
Thank you so much.

18:08.019 --> 18:09.885
I am going to get us a booth.

18:09.887 --> 18:10.788
- Okay.
- Okay.

18:12.257 --> 18:14.957
And what would
you like?

18:14.959 --> 18:18.928
Um, which do you prefer better,
the chocolate or the vanilla?

18:18.930 --> 18:20.062
EMPLOYEE:
The swirl.

18:20.064 --> 18:21.529
- SCOTT: Swirl?
- EMPLOYEE: Swirl.

18:21.531 --> 18:24.100
- Swirl!
- It's vanilla and chocolate together.

18:24.102 --> 18:27.437
SCOTT: Okay, so it's all mixed up.
Like you?

18:27.439 --> 18:29.271
- EMPLOYEE: Yeah, like me.
- SCOTT: Okay.

18:29.273 --> 18:31.274
- Okay.
- Let me give you a taste.

18:31.276 --> 18:32.411
I'll taste it.

18:33.278 --> 18:34.509
Okay, so...

18:34.511 --> 18:37.412
So now it's
like a crime to talk?

18:37.414 --> 18:39.382
I don't have a problem
with you talking.

18:39.384 --> 18:41.084
It's the way
that you were talking.

18:41.086 --> 18:42.651
It's the what?

18:42.653 --> 18:45.220
It's the way
that you were talking.

18:45.222 --> 18:47.222
She just asked me
what flavor I wanted.

18:47.224 --> 18:50.392
And it seemed like you might as
well have just given her a lick.

18:50.394 --> 18:55.198
Can we just move on
with our day?

18:55.200 --> 18:59.471
You know, maybe snuggle
on the couch a little bit?

19:03.240 --> 19:04.343
Apparently not.

19:11.481 --> 19:13.951
Annie, I left this on.
Did you turn it off?

19:17.654 --> 19:19.456
[♪♪♪]

19:19.458 --> 19:22.491
So, essentially, when life
calls for that recharge,

19:22.493 --> 19:24.163
you reach for Recover 180.

19:26.498 --> 19:28.096
- MIKE: You see?
- [PHONE VIBRATING]

19:28.098 --> 19:30.799
It sells itself, and what
we do is, we hammer that home

19:30.801 --> 19:33.169
with the advertising that
already exists on the bottle.

19:33.171 --> 19:35.205
Twice the electrolytes
at half of the calories.

19:35.207 --> 19:38.641
- Scott's come up with a theory.
- I gotta take this.

19:38.643 --> 19:42.311
MIKE: Scott has a really interesting
idea for a dual campaign.

19:42.313 --> 19:44.013
This is called
the cloud kicker...

19:44.015 --> 19:45.217
Hey, baby, what's up?

19:46.617 --> 19:48.351
You're not gonna believe this.

19:48.353 --> 19:50.986
Charlie is outside
cutting the grass.

19:50.988 --> 19:53.155
Wait, wait. What?

19:53.157 --> 19:55.790
ANNIE: <i>Charlie's
outside mowing our lawn.</i>

19:55.792 --> 19:57.994
Literally, right now.

19:57.996 --> 20:00.098
- SCOTT: <i>Why?</i>
- I don't know.

20:02.834 --> 20:04.236
Uh, I'll call you back, honey.

20:05.670 --> 20:06.572
Okay.

20:11.675 --> 20:12.674
ANNIE:
Charlie!

20:12.676 --> 20:14.346
- Hey, hey.
- Hi.

20:17.315 --> 20:20.350
- Good morning.
- What are you doing?

20:20.352 --> 20:21.684
- What?
- What are you doing?

20:21.686 --> 20:23.385
Oh. Heh.

20:23.387 --> 20:27.690
Well, I noticed that the grass
was getting out of hand, and...

20:27.692 --> 20:29.459
You really gotta
keep up with this.

20:29.461 --> 20:31.693
So I just...
I just went ahead.

20:31.695 --> 20:33.662
Did you just get this
out of the garage?

20:33.664 --> 20:34.799
That's where I keep it.

20:36.099 --> 20:38.100
Huh.
What happened to Florida?

20:38.102 --> 20:39.634
I thought you'd be
gone by now.

20:39.636 --> 20:41.136
Well, you know, it...

20:41.138 --> 20:44.007
Moving is a lot harder
than I thought.

20:44.009 --> 20:46.676
I had, uh... I have a lot
of loose ends.

20:46.678 --> 20:48.611
I'm gonna be leaving soon.

20:48.613 --> 20:52.448
Yeah. Yeah, it's hard to...
Hard to say goodbye.

20:52.450 --> 20:53.849
- Yeah, I bet.
- Mm-hm.

20:53.851 --> 20:55.250
Where are you staying?

20:55.252 --> 20:56.585
I'm at The Royal.

20:56.587 --> 20:58.421
It's a little hotel

20:58.423 --> 21:00.389
just right in the middle
of the village.

21:00.391 --> 21:01.923
Right. Right, right.

21:01.925 --> 21:05.527
You know, Charlie,
I appreciate what you're doing,

21:05.529 --> 21:08.398
but you don't have to do this.
We've got it.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.565
Oh! Oh.

21:09.567 --> 21:11.433
Here's the reason I came by.

21:11.435 --> 21:13.436
Here's a list
of local numbers.

21:13.438 --> 21:16.037
Plumber, an electrician,
emergency numbers.

21:16.039 --> 21:17.707
Thought you might
want to have it.

21:17.709 --> 21:19.275
You know we can
Google this now?

21:19.277 --> 21:21.143
Yeah, but these people
know the house,

21:21.145 --> 21:23.411
and they're not gonna
gouge you on the price.

21:23.413 --> 21:25.113
You can't get that
on the Internet.

21:25.115 --> 21:27.152
- You can't get that.
- No, you can't.

21:28.553 --> 21:31.720
ANNIE:
Well, he did a pretty good job.

21:31.722 --> 21:33.788
He also said
it's probably the last time

21:33.790 --> 21:35.924
the lawn will need
to be mowed this year,

21:35.926 --> 21:38.061
and he left the grass seed
and the spreader

21:38.063 --> 21:39.728
at the front
of the storage shed

21:39.730 --> 21:41.463
so that you could find it
in April,

21:41.465 --> 21:43.799
and that you're gonna want
to use steer manure,

21:43.801 --> 21:45.567
but that,
you should buy that fresh.

21:45.569 --> 21:48.771
Oh, yeah, yeah. When I do
my spring planting. Yeah.

21:48.773 --> 21:51.142
- [CHUCKLES]
- Eh...

21:52.777 --> 21:54.276
Is that it?

21:54.278 --> 21:56.478
I feel like you're not
telling me everything,

21:56.480 --> 21:58.080
so spit it out.

21:58.082 --> 22:00.749
I invited him
to Thanksgiving.

22:00.751 --> 22:02.619
- What?
- It just slipped out of my mouth,

22:02.621 --> 22:04.821
but you should've seen
how happy it made him.

22:04.823 --> 22:06.255
Baby, we don't know him.

22:06.257 --> 22:08.458
I know, but he's lonely,

22:08.460 --> 22:10.259
and he doesn't
have any family here,

22:10.261 --> 22:12.596
and he's getting ready
to be gone anyways, and...

22:13.663 --> 22:14.598
Yeah.

22:16.835 --> 22:18.734
Anything else?

22:18.736 --> 22:20.339
He's gonna bring the pies.

22:25.509 --> 22:26.942
He's gonna bring some pies.

22:26.944 --> 22:29.312
- He's gonna bring some pies.
- Is that right? Okay.

22:29.314 --> 22:32.614
- Evidently.
- Oh, that makes it all better.

22:32.616 --> 22:35.017
<i>♪ Little and perfect ♪</i>

22:35.019 --> 22:37.687
<i>♪ Behind the curtains ♪</i>

22:37.689 --> 22:39.787
<i>♪ Moving too close ♪</i>

22:39.789 --> 22:42.292
<i>♪ Want to unfold ♪</i>

22:42.294 --> 22:45.827
<i>♪ But what if I tell you... ♪</i>

22:45.829 --> 22:47.697
Okay, the doctor's here.

22:47.699 --> 22:49.097
Let's do it.

22:49.099 --> 22:50.932
- Don't drop it.
- All right, here we go.

22:50.934 --> 22:52.200
[GRUNTS]

22:52.202 --> 22:53.803
- Okay.
- Yes.

22:53.805 --> 22:55.537
- Boom. What does that look like?
- Yes.

22:55.539 --> 22:56.838
- Is it good?
- Perfect.

22:56.840 --> 22:58.075
We made it.

22:59.477 --> 23:00.709
Mm!

23:00.711 --> 23:02.978
Well...

23:02.980 --> 23:04.313
ANNIE:
Stop.

23:04.315 --> 23:06.516
Oh, okay.

23:06.518 --> 23:08.553
Hey, the Bambi killer's here.

23:10.554 --> 23:11.821
Hey, Scott.

23:11.823 --> 23:13.521
- How's it going?
- Happy Thanksgiving.

23:13.523 --> 23:15.457
- You too.
- Hey. Thanks for the invite.

23:15.459 --> 23:16.892
It was her idea. Come on in.

23:16.894 --> 23:18.661
- Hi, Charlie.
- Hello.

23:18.663 --> 23:20.395
How are you?

23:20.397 --> 23:22.565
Wow,
the house feels so alive.

23:22.567 --> 23:24.065
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

23:24.067 --> 23:25.901
- Here, as promised.
- Oh, perfect.

23:25.903 --> 23:27.402
I got an apple and a pumpkin.

23:27.404 --> 23:29.004
Oh, I love pumpkin.

23:29.006 --> 23:31.640
- Oh, smells so good.
- It's definitely going down.

23:31.642 --> 23:32.642
- Uh-uh.
- Okay.

23:32.644 --> 23:33.875
I'm gonna finish.

23:33.877 --> 23:35.878
Okay. Okay.

23:35.880 --> 23:38.014
You really know
how to make a house a home.

23:38.016 --> 23:39.849
- Thank you, Charlie.
- SCOTT: Come on.

23:39.851 --> 23:42.051
I'll show you
what progress we've made.

23:42.053 --> 23:44.186
Look, we still got
a couple more rooms to...

23:44.188 --> 23:45.622
- To paint and everything.
- Yeah.

23:45.624 --> 23:47.055
But we're pretty close.

23:47.057 --> 23:49.592
- It's a work in progress.
- Oh, my.

23:49.594 --> 23:51.759
Oh, wow.

23:51.761 --> 23:53.261
- Yeah.
- Jeepers.

23:53.263 --> 23:55.396
I could just get lost in that.

23:55.398 --> 23:57.234
- Just take a look around.
- Okay.

23:58.869 --> 24:02.871
Annie said that your trip
got delayed to Florida.

24:02.873 --> 24:05.544
So you're still around
for a little while, huh?

24:06.778 --> 24:09.210
Yes, uh, my daughter,
Cassidy,

24:09.212 --> 24:13.449
she wants to fix up
a special room for me there.

24:13.451 --> 24:16.119
Of course,
it has to be perfect.

24:16.121 --> 24:19.958
But, uh, that's my Cassidy.
She's Daddy's little girl.

24:22.058 --> 24:22.961
So, uh...

24:24.295 --> 24:25.263
Here you go.

24:28.633 --> 24:32.168
- What happened to the tapestry?
- The what?

24:32.170 --> 24:34.803
The tapestry that conveyed
with the house.

24:34.805 --> 24:36.939
It was my gift to you.

24:36.941 --> 24:40.142
Oh, yes, yes, yes, um...

24:40.144 --> 24:43.845
Didn't really feel like
it was us, you know?

24:43.847 --> 24:47.482
This painting, though, this is
what makes Annie really happy.

24:47.484 --> 24:51.054
Something that we bought
when we first got married.

24:51.056 --> 24:53.622
She likes to see this
every morning when we wake up,

24:53.624 --> 24:55.290
and I can't blame her.

24:55.292 --> 24:57.061
It's pretty stunning,
don't you think?

24:59.596 --> 25:01.796
Yeah, it's not for everybody.

25:01.798 --> 25:04.167
We were talking about
changing the floors.

25:04.169 --> 25:07.068
[VOICE FADING] Maybe go with
a dark wood throughout, but...

25:07.070 --> 25:08.304
[♪♪♪]

25:08.306 --> 25:10.305
I haven't quite gotten
to that yet, so...

25:10.307 --> 25:11.874
<i>[HEART BEATING,
HEAVY BREATHING]</i>

25:11.876 --> 25:13.875
[MUFFLED, DISTORTED]
We'll figure it out.

25:13.877 --> 25:15.143
That's it.

25:15.145 --> 25:16.778
We got to make it our own,
right?

25:16.780 --> 25:19.748
That's what...
That's what we're here for.

25:19.750 --> 25:21.553
[CLEARS THROAT]

25:23.421 --> 25:26.725
[NORMALLY] Well, happy Thanksgiving, man.
What should we toast to?

25:28.358 --> 25:30.226
- [ALL LAUGHING]
- Here's to Annie's meal.

25:30.228 --> 25:32.394
- Here's to Annie.
- CHARLIE: To your new house.

25:32.396 --> 25:35.264
- All that hard work.
- Happy Thanksgiving.

25:35.266 --> 25:37.699
I'm so happy for you guys.
Oh, this is great.

25:37.701 --> 25:40.635
First of all, we just want
to thank you guys for being here

25:40.637 --> 25:43.037
on our first Thanksgiving
in our new home.

25:43.039 --> 25:44.707
When you're done with
the changes,

25:44.709 --> 25:45.908
the place will be great.

25:45.910 --> 25:47.677
Oh, really? Really?

25:47.679 --> 25:49.844
- Break out this back wall, right?
- Totally.

25:49.846 --> 25:52.280
MIKE: You guys are
wasting square footage.

25:52.282 --> 25:55.684
That dining room in there,
it's small by modern standards,

25:55.686 --> 25:57.152
but if you start expanding it

25:57.154 --> 25:58.853
and knocking it out
and everything,

25:58.855 --> 26:02.356
you're gonna... You're gonna
ruin the integrity of it.

26:02.358 --> 26:05.526
- Houses have integrity?
- Of course they do, Mike.

26:05.528 --> 26:07.162
- MIKE: Yeah?
- CHARLIE: Yes.

26:07.164 --> 26:09.565
- Some people don't, but...
- Oh...!

26:09.567 --> 26:13.068
At least the houses worth
living in do, that's for sure.

26:13.070 --> 26:14.737
I was a structural engineer.

26:14.739 --> 26:16.572
I don't know
if Scott told you that.

26:16.574 --> 26:17.672
That's... I'm retired.

26:17.674 --> 26:19.107
I built roads and bridges,

26:19.109 --> 26:21.344
and I believe that
every one of them I built,

26:21.346 --> 26:23.412
- I put my soul into it.
- Mm.

26:23.414 --> 26:26.715
And I believe that
they have souls themselves.

26:26.717 --> 26:28.651
Bullshit.

26:28.653 --> 26:31.053
- Mike. Stop it.
- Listen, I think he has a point.

26:31.055 --> 26:33.956
But isn't this kind of
the way of the world?

26:33.958 --> 26:36.726
Out with the old,
in with the new.

26:36.728 --> 26:38.760
Let's rebuild the Taj Mahal,
huh?

26:38.762 --> 26:41.196
This is not the Taj Mahal,
Charlie.

26:41.198 --> 26:43.032
- You're a little crazy.
- RACHEL: Right?

26:43.034 --> 26:44.499
You having trouble with that?

26:44.501 --> 26:45.801
Just give me a minute.

26:45.803 --> 26:47.135
Hey, Charlie, top me off.

26:47.137 --> 26:49.106
- I'm gonna go out for a smoke.
- Sure.

26:51.307 --> 26:53.111
All of it. Giddyup, cowboy.

26:55.880 --> 26:56.911
Thanks, Charlie.

26:56.913 --> 26:59.817
[♪♪♪]

27:02.653 --> 27:04.420
ANNIE:
Charlie, no! No!

27:04.422 --> 27:05.886
[GROANS]

27:05.888 --> 27:08.125
Why would you do that?

27:09.794 --> 27:11.229
[CHUCKLES]

27:14.065 --> 27:16.732
- Ah! Got it.
- All right.

27:16.734 --> 27:18.400
Hey,
let's give a hand for Scott.

27:18.402 --> 27:20.105
- There you go.
- All right.

27:22.173 --> 27:23.972
Who's having white?

27:23.974 --> 27:25.909
[♪♪♪]

27:32.250 --> 27:33.782
CHARLIE:
Ooh.

27:33.784 --> 27:35.151
Needed some fresh air.

27:35.153 --> 27:36.818
[CHUCKLES]

27:36.820 --> 27:38.187
What a meal, right?

27:38.189 --> 27:40.756
- Oh, Annie, she's a great cook.
- Yeah.

27:40.758 --> 27:41.992
Oh.

27:43.327 --> 27:45.628
- Smoke, Charlie?
- Oh, no, thanks.

27:45.630 --> 27:46.998
Gave it up 30 years ago.

27:50.434 --> 27:51.669
[SOFTLY]
Good for you.

27:54.338 --> 27:56.707
[NORMALLY] Must have been
hard to give all this up.

27:58.174 --> 28:00.010
Yes, it was.

28:01.679 --> 28:03.344
Trust me.

28:03.346 --> 28:05.250
[♪♪♪]

28:08.352 --> 28:09.254
Have you?

28:10.354 --> 28:11.453
What?

28:11.455 --> 28:14.021
Given it up.

28:14.023 --> 28:16.193
Scott said you came over
to mow their grass.

28:18.296 --> 28:20.028
Had to be done.

28:20.030 --> 28:22.564
Grass was getting
out of control.

28:22.566 --> 28:25.034
So you keep an eye
on the place. That it?

28:25.036 --> 28:26.004
Mm.

28:27.771 --> 28:29.907
Drive by from time to time,
yeah.

28:33.810 --> 28:35.679
And I also hunt.

28:37.315 --> 28:38.883
Right here in these woods.

28:45.789 --> 28:47.623
You ever hunt at night,
Charlie?

28:47.625 --> 28:49.892
[CHUCKLING]

28:49.894 --> 28:51.492
Mike...

28:51.494 --> 28:53.661
hunting after dark
is illegal.

28:53.663 --> 28:55.163
Oh, okay.

28:55.165 --> 28:56.800
- Because I don't know.
- Yeah.

29:02.673 --> 29:04.539
Oh, what am I doing?

29:04.541 --> 29:06.709
Wouldn't want to ruin
your nice lawn.

29:06.711 --> 29:08.212
[SCOFFS]

29:16.688 --> 29:18.888
I'll toss it in the garbage.

29:18.890 --> 29:20.225
See you inside, Charlie.

29:21.424 --> 29:22.326
Nice vest.

29:24.194 --> 29:26.061
[SIGHS]

29:26.063 --> 29:27.966
[♪♪♪]

29:30.401 --> 29:31.400
ANNIE:
Great.

29:31.402 --> 29:32.770
CHARLIE:
Oh.

29:34.605 --> 29:38.739
That was probably the best meal
ever made in this house.

29:38.741 --> 29:41.142
And good thing
because I made you a doggie bag.

29:41.144 --> 29:43.045
This is gonna be gone
before midnight.

29:43.047 --> 29:45.113
You truly are
the lady of the house.

29:45.115 --> 29:46.180
Thank you.

29:46.182 --> 29:47.716
Enjoy the food.

29:47.718 --> 29:49.617
Have a great
rest of the evening.

29:49.619 --> 29:52.788
ANNIE: Have a great
retirement in Florida.

29:52.790 --> 29:55.257
[MOCKINGLY]
"Enjoy your retirement."

29:55.259 --> 29:57.226
SCOTT:
<i>Hey. Mike's drunk.</i>

29:57.228 --> 29:59.594
- I just had a theory.
- Tell them what you told me.

29:59.596 --> 30:01.729
- All right. I'm gonna tell you.
- Go ahead.

30:01.731 --> 30:03.097
- Annie.
- What? What?

30:03.099 --> 30:04.565
I think it was
that old dude

30:04.567 --> 30:06.768
who put the cigarette burns
in my upholstery.

30:06.770 --> 30:09.771
- What? Charlie?
- Mm-hm.

30:09.773 --> 30:11.140
ANNIE:
Why would he do that?

30:11.142 --> 30:13.307
Because,
and I apologize ahead of time,

30:13.309 --> 30:15.111
when I went out
to have a smoke,

30:15.113 --> 30:17.045
- I took a piss on your roses.
- Of course.

30:17.047 --> 30:18.646
We got four
different bathrooms...

30:18.648 --> 30:19.949
MIKE:
Here's the point.

30:19.951 --> 30:22.918
Charlie thinks
those are his roses.

30:22.920 --> 30:24.920
He thinks
that I defiled his lawn.

30:24.922 --> 30:26.621
He still thinks
this is his house.

30:26.623 --> 30:27.856
How would he know?

30:27.858 --> 30:29.624
- He's watching from the woods.
- Okay.

30:29.626 --> 30:31.759
- Come on, man.
- Okay.

30:31.761 --> 30:34.930
Look, Scott, I bet you,
if we went out into the woods,

30:34.932 --> 30:37.165
we would find proof
that I was right.

30:37.167 --> 30:39.168
Wanna put your money
where your mouth is?

30:39.170 --> 30:41.170
- Yeah. How much?
- Five.

30:41.172 --> 30:43.171
- Don't do it.
- Five hundred. Let's do it.

30:43.173 --> 30:45.474
- That's a bet.
- Oh, God.

30:45.476 --> 30:47.642
SCOTT: There's a senior
citizen in the woods.

30:47.644 --> 30:49.612
We gonna take care of this
for you.

30:49.614 --> 30:51.314
ANNIE:
Good luck!

30:51.316 --> 30:53.315
- MIKE: Oh, yeah.
- SCOTT: Okay, tough guy.

30:53.317 --> 30:55.283
- MIKE: That's right, baby.
- SCOTT: This...

30:55.285 --> 30:56.686
[BOTH LAUGHING]

30:56.688 --> 30:58.987
This is some Scooby-Doo shit
right here.

30:58.989 --> 31:00.355
Scooby-Doo?

31:00.357 --> 31:02.423
Why did you move
all the way out here?

31:02.425 --> 31:04.660
We had it wired
back in the city.

31:04.662 --> 31:07.498
You know, Annie wanted
to start a family.

31:08.865 --> 31:10.067
I love her, so...

31:11.368 --> 31:12.269
What's wrong?

31:14.305 --> 31:17.373
You can see right
into the house from here.

31:17.375 --> 31:18.308
Told you.

31:24.280 --> 31:25.913
Look at that. Scott.

31:25.915 --> 31:28.249
There's a path that leads
right into the woods.

31:28.251 --> 31:30.052
Okay,
that's where he shot Bambi.

31:30.054 --> 31:31.219
Right over there, man.

31:31.221 --> 31:33.391
So where do you think he is?
Come on.

31:35.726 --> 31:37.959
- You sure about this?
- Come on.

31:37.961 --> 31:39.795
How much you wanna bet
they got lost?

31:39.797 --> 31:40.895
Don't even tell me.

31:40.897 --> 31:42.430
Maybe we should have
given them

31:42.432 --> 31:44.032
some bread crumbs
or something,

31:44.034 --> 31:45.167
find their way home.

31:45.169 --> 31:46.334
[LAUGHS]

31:46.336 --> 31:47.872
What did you think
about Charlie?

31:49.573 --> 31:51.840
I think he's...

31:51.842 --> 31:54.643
- kind of hot for an older guy.
- What?

31:54.645 --> 31:55.878
- Rachel.
- Oh, come on.

31:55.880 --> 31:57.513
Tell me you don't
think so too.

31:57.515 --> 32:00.181
No. Okay. You know what it is?
I think it's this...

32:00.183 --> 32:02.250
The manly man thing
that he has, you know?

32:02.252 --> 32:04.352
Like, it's something
our grandfathers had

32:04.354 --> 32:06.254
and our dads had.

32:06.256 --> 32:07.989
I don't know.
I feel sorry for him.

32:07.991 --> 32:09.892
He's such a sweetheart.

32:09.894 --> 32:11.326
Our poor city boys.

32:11.328 --> 32:13.128
RACHEL:
<i>You know they're lost, right?</i>

32:13.130 --> 32:14.796
SCOTT: This looks like
some sort of fire road.

32:14.798 --> 32:16.231
MIKE:
That's convenient, huh?

32:16.233 --> 32:18.100
Charlie parks the car,
leaves it here,

32:18.102 --> 32:19.301
walks through the woods.

32:19.303 --> 32:21.170
He's at your place
in no time.

32:21.172 --> 32:22.640
Look,
there's fresh tire tracks.

32:25.576 --> 32:26.842
Might be
hunters, man.

32:26.844 --> 32:28.746
There's hunters out here
in these woods.

32:30.547 --> 32:31.449
Who's that?

32:33.150 --> 32:35.887
[ENGINE REVVING]

32:37.054 --> 32:39.121
Is he coming at us?

32:39.123 --> 32:43.025
No, he's backing away.
Scott, he's backing away.

32:43.027 --> 32:45.093
- So what? We going? We going?
- Hey!

32:45.095 --> 32:47.962
[♪♪♪]

32:47.964 --> 32:49.701
[TIRES SQUEALING]

32:54.204 --> 32:55.105
Who was that?

32:56.707 --> 32:58.609
[TOOL WHIRRING]

33:03.748 --> 33:05.850
This is not
how I saw us living here.

33:06.983 --> 33:08.883
Me either.

33:08.885 --> 33:10.989
I just feel like
this is unnecessary.

33:12.388 --> 33:13.654
Annie.

33:13.656 --> 33:15.356
You want this tied
to your landline

33:15.358 --> 33:16.326
or your cell phones?

33:17.627 --> 33:19.830
Cell phones. Thank you.

33:24.067 --> 33:25.633
- Oh, shit.
- CHARLIE: Hey! Hey!

33:25.635 --> 33:27.569
- This guy.
- CHARLIE: Randall!

33:27.571 --> 33:29.238
Stop drilling holes
in my house.

33:29.240 --> 33:31.806
- Hey, hey. Keep working.
- What the hell are you doing?

33:31.808 --> 33:33.007
What are you doing here?

33:33.009 --> 33:34.776
I was down the road.
I was fishing.

33:34.778 --> 33:37.813
I saw the security van
go by.

33:37.815 --> 33:39.847
You been having a problem?

33:39.849 --> 33:42.683
Look,
I got a prowler in the woods.

33:42.685 --> 33:43.952
It's kids.

33:43.954 --> 33:46.188
- What kids?
- It's high school kids.

33:46.190 --> 33:49.524
They sneak out into these woods,
and they party after dark.

33:49.526 --> 33:51.125
- No.
- This is not necessary.

33:51.127 --> 33:54.430
What is necessary is
that I protect my wife.

33:54.432 --> 33:57.332
If you wanna protect your wife,
get a gun.

33:57.334 --> 33:59.468
No guns on my property.

33:59.470 --> 34:00.969
[SIGHS]

34:00.971 --> 34:02.069
You understand?

34:02.071 --> 34:04.206
What do you got
against guns?

34:04.208 --> 34:06.208
I know what guns can do,

34:06.210 --> 34:07.910
and I'm not talking
about killing

34:07.912 --> 34:10.210
a defenseless deer
in the woods, okay?

34:10.213 --> 34:13.347
When I was 12, my brother was
gunned down in the street.

34:13.349 --> 34:16.351
I know what guns can do,
Charlie.

34:16.353 --> 34:17.688
I'm sorry for your loss.

34:20.324 --> 34:21.458
Enjoy Florida.

34:23.159 --> 34:25.393
Hey, Randall. You be careful
with these vines.

34:25.396 --> 34:28.496
It took 50 years for these
things to grow on the house.

34:28.498 --> 34:29.567
RANDALL:
Okay, Mr. Peck.

34:30.701 --> 34:32.166
It's not your house.

34:32.168 --> 34:35.072
[♪♪♪]

34:45.547 --> 34:47.217
[CREAKING SOFTLY]

34:52.056 --> 34:54.222
[SIGHS]

34:54.224 --> 34:55.625
Babe, what are you doing?

34:58.795 --> 35:00.063
[SIGHS]

35:01.699 --> 35:02.900
I can't sleep.

35:04.233 --> 35:06.603
I keep hearing
this creaking sound.

35:08.672 --> 35:10.775
Honey, it's an old house.

35:12.076 --> 35:13.744
Creaking is what they do.

35:16.914 --> 35:18.382
[CREAKING CONTINUES]

35:22.485 --> 35:24.422
[♪♪♪]

35:31.594 --> 35:32.496
ANNIE:
Scott!

35:34.130 --> 35:35.031
Scott?

35:39.936 --> 35:42.639
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

35:48.711 --> 35:50.278
[ENGINE STARTS]

35:50.280 --> 35:52.180
GIRL:
Let's go! Get in the truck!

35:52.182 --> 35:54.117
[GIRL WHOOPS]

36:01.157 --> 36:02.360
Oh, come on.

36:16.139 --> 36:19.042
[♪♪♪]

36:22.378 --> 36:25.215
<i>♪ This time of the year ♪</i>

36:27.117 --> 36:28.385
What is he doing now?

36:29.820 --> 36:31.153
I thought he left.

36:31.155 --> 36:33.024
I don't know.

36:35.291 --> 36:36.594
SCOTT:
Why is he in the shed?

36:41.130 --> 36:43.197
- Just stay in the car.
- Scott.

36:43.199 --> 36:45.300
- Hey, Scott. I was out...
- Put the gun away!

36:45.302 --> 36:48.036
All right, all right.
I was hunting along the creek.

36:48.038 --> 36:50.805
The deer tore up
your flower bed.

36:50.807 --> 36:53.307
I was just getting
potting soil, Scott.

36:53.309 --> 36:54.309
Charlie.

36:54.311 --> 36:55.911
Charlie...

36:55.913 --> 36:59.079
No guns on my property.
I've asked you that.

36:59.081 --> 37:01.650
Anybody can hunt along
the creek. Not just me.

37:01.652 --> 37:03.251
- Anybody.
- Charlie, I'm telling you

37:03.253 --> 37:04.885
right now, you.

37:04.887 --> 37:06.987
No guns on my property ever.

37:06.989 --> 37:08.523
- All right, Scott.
- Ever.

37:08.525 --> 37:10.358
I didn't mean to ruin
your afternoon.

37:10.360 --> 37:11.929
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Annie, I...

37:14.532 --> 37:17.365
- Is that a spruce?
- It's a Christmas tree, Charlie.

37:17.367 --> 37:20.068
Well, they don't lose
their needles so quick.

37:20.070 --> 37:22.304
Here, let me help you with that.
Here you go.

37:22.306 --> 37:24.008
Here. Use this.

37:28.179 --> 37:29.247
There you go.

37:31.782 --> 37:34.849
Did you find
the Christmas decorations yet?

37:34.851 --> 37:35.950
No.

37:35.952 --> 37:38.155
Oh, you've gotta
see this.

37:40.391 --> 37:41.688
Oh, my God.

37:41.690 --> 37:43.391
All that for one tree, huh?

37:43.393 --> 37:46.528
No, most of these lights are
for the outside of the house.

37:46.530 --> 37:48.162
Honey,
do you see all this stuff?

37:48.164 --> 37:49.664
- Yeah, I see it.
- Here.

37:49.666 --> 37:51.398
Let's get this inside,
I'll show you what's what.

37:51.400 --> 37:52.534
- Yeah, yeah.
- No, no, no.

37:52.536 --> 37:53.901
Look, Charlie,
Annie and I

37:53.903 --> 37:55.804
will take care of this
on our own time.

37:55.806 --> 37:57.371
Thank you.

37:57.373 --> 37:59.474
CHARLIE: But I'm just trying to
help, Scott.

37:59.476 --> 38:00.909
Yeah.
I appreciate your help,

38:00.911 --> 38:03.043
but, look, the next time
you wanna stop by,

38:03.045 --> 38:05.213
you call or you text first.

38:05.215 --> 38:06.516
You don't just show up.

38:08.452 --> 38:10.217
Oh...

38:10.219 --> 38:11.420
Hey, I'm sorry.

38:11.422 --> 38:13.354
I'm sure where you come from,

38:13.356 --> 38:15.289
people don't just drop by,
do they?

38:15.291 --> 38:17.092
- No.
- No. All right.

38:17.094 --> 38:19.461
I'll honor that. We good?

38:19.463 --> 38:21.132
We're good, Charlie.

38:22.733 --> 38:23.768
We're good.

38:27.137 --> 38:28.839
Merry Christmas, Annie.

38:29.672 --> 38:30.607
Thank you.

38:34.644 --> 38:36.077
Honey,
what is the problem?

38:36.079 --> 38:37.945
Something is really off
with that guy.

38:37.947 --> 38:40.014
Do you have to make him
feel so unwelcome?

38:40.016 --> 38:42.383
He is unwelcome.
He spies on us from the woods.

38:42.385 --> 38:44.753
You said you went back there
and you heard kids.

38:44.755 --> 38:46.457
Okay, that one time,
yes, but...

38:48.125 --> 38:49.925
Look,
whose side are you on?

38:49.927 --> 38:51.362
Whose side am I...?

38:52.630 --> 38:54.229
What is really
the problem here?

38:54.231 --> 38:56.632
The man acts like
the house still belongs to him.

38:56.634 --> 38:58.467
Oh, my God.

38:58.469 --> 39:00.334
Come on, Scott.
Give the guy a break.

39:00.336 --> 39:03.271
He's lost his wife.
He lost his house.

39:03.273 --> 39:05.206
SCOTT:
This is our house, not his.

39:05.208 --> 39:07.608
- He doesn't live here anymore.
- ANNIE: I get that.

39:07.610 --> 39:10.311
SCOTT: I drive an hour and a
half to the city every day,

39:10.313 --> 39:11.546
and I'm back every night.

39:11.548 --> 39:12.880
I get up, I go to work,

39:12.882 --> 39:14.316
I come home, I go to bed,

39:14.318 --> 39:16.418
and then I go
back to work again.

39:16.420 --> 39:18.820
How is this place
supposed to feel like it's mine

39:18.822 --> 39:20.191
if he won't leave?

39:23.260 --> 39:25.025
Do you still want this?

39:25.027 --> 39:27.262
- What?
- Do you still want this?

39:27.264 --> 39:28.829
Still want what?

39:28.831 --> 39:31.166
This. Our home.

39:31.168 --> 39:34.171
I just need some time
to adjust.

39:35.572 --> 39:36.907
Because I love it here.

39:38.708 --> 39:39.609
I know.

39:43.547 --> 39:44.545
Okay.

39:44.547 --> 39:46.483
[♪♪♪]

40:03.099 --> 40:05.666
SCOTT: We can agree these
fourth-quarter numbers,

40:05.668 --> 40:07.168
they're staggering.

40:07.170 --> 40:08.704
Thank you for a great meeting.

40:08.706 --> 40:10.871
- MAN: Thanks.
- Congratulations, Scott.

40:10.873 --> 40:13.608
They all believe
that you're a marketing genius.

40:13.610 --> 40:15.880
Yeah, that was, uh...
That was part of the plan.

40:17.514 --> 40:20.349
Ms. Richards, one thing
you should know about me.

40:20.351 --> 40:23.253
I am very passionate
about what I do.

40:24.688 --> 40:26.190
You won't be disappointed.

40:29.659 --> 40:30.560
Jillian.

40:33.364 --> 40:34.264
Jillian.

40:36.432 --> 40:40.135
A few of us are gonna go
and have a drink afterwards.

40:40.137 --> 40:41.639
Would you like to join us?

40:48.445 --> 40:50.778
- Season's greetings, Annie.
- [GASPS]

40:50.780 --> 40:53.113
- Charlie.
- Hi.

40:53.115 --> 40:54.383
Hi.

40:54.385 --> 40:57.119
I brought you and Scott
a bottle of wine

40:57.121 --> 40:59.354
from my neighbor's vineyard.

40:59.356 --> 41:00.787
Oh, wow.

41:00.789 --> 41:04.492
I wanna make amends
for causing any kind of drama.

41:04.494 --> 41:06.394
Thank you. It's okay.

41:06.396 --> 41:08.496
I tried to call him.

41:08.498 --> 41:11.267
But his cell phone said
his mailbox was full.

41:13.336 --> 41:15.170
- About the other day...
- Yeah.

41:15.172 --> 41:16.604
That wasn't your fault.

41:16.606 --> 41:18.106
Scott's brother was killed,

41:18.108 --> 41:19.608
and it's a trigger for him.

41:19.610 --> 41:21.208
- Guns are...
- Yeah. Yes.

41:21.210 --> 41:23.911
It must have been devastating
for him, so I understand.

41:23.913 --> 41:25.648
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah.

41:27.251 --> 41:29.153
So you're putting up the lights,
are you?

41:30.320 --> 41:32.720
I am. I am.

41:32.722 --> 41:34.755
- Beautiful job so far.
- Thank you.

41:34.757 --> 41:36.826
- You're doing this by yourself?
- Yes.

41:39.829 --> 41:40.965
Do you want to help?

41:42.032 --> 41:43.365
- Oh, yeah.
- ANNIE: Nice.

41:43.367 --> 41:45.833
- Teamwork makes the dream work.
- Yeah.

41:45.835 --> 41:47.501
- Hopefully we can...
- Where is Scott?

41:47.503 --> 41:49.637
Uh... Actually, no.

41:49.639 --> 41:51.104
- He's at work.
- Yeah?

41:51.106 --> 41:52.840
Yeah, he'll be home later.

41:52.842 --> 41:55.175
[♪♪♪]

41:55.177 --> 41:57.646
- Thank you so much for the help.
- [CHUCKLING]

41:57.648 --> 41:59.780
- Glad to do it.
- You want something to drink?

41:59.782 --> 42:01.349
Um...

42:01.351 --> 42:03.617
Would you like me to open
this bottle of wine?

42:03.619 --> 42:06.054
It needs to breathe anyway
before Scott gets home.

42:06.056 --> 42:08.858
- Yeah, that's a great idea.
- You know? All right.

42:12.829 --> 42:14.164
Okay.

42:16.400 --> 42:19.300
You don't really strike me
as a city girl.

42:19.302 --> 42:21.470
- You could tell?
- Hm.

42:21.472 --> 42:23.304
I grew up in a small town
in Indiana,

42:23.306 --> 42:25.173
so I'm really
a country girl at heart.

42:25.175 --> 42:26.874
- Really?
- Yeah.

42:26.876 --> 42:28.642
The city's great,
if you're single

42:28.644 --> 42:30.445
and you're young, but...

42:30.447 --> 42:32.813
I wanna raise my kids
in the clean, fresh air.

42:32.815 --> 42:35.916
- So you are gonna have kids.
- Yeah.

42:35.918 --> 42:37.217
You got any glasses?

42:37.219 --> 42:38.987
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Sorry about that.

42:38.989 --> 42:41.889
Nobody tells you
how hard it is

42:41.891 --> 42:44.258
to raise children,
that's for sure.

42:44.260 --> 42:47.996
I mean, I know that my kids

42:47.998 --> 42:50.565
- caused a few gray hairs on my head.
- [LAUGHS]

42:50.567 --> 42:51.898
You know, in the end,

42:51.900 --> 42:54.034
children
are your biggest challenge

42:54.036 --> 42:56.873
that you will ever have
and the greatest blessing.

42:58.876 --> 42:59.874
Amen.

42:59.876 --> 43:01.242
[WINE POURING]

43:01.244 --> 43:02.179
Cheers?

43:03.246 --> 43:04.414
- Cheers.
- [GLASSES CLINK]

43:05.882 --> 43:07.585
- [PHONE CHIMES]
- Mm.

43:09.686 --> 43:11.221
That needs to breathe.

43:15.958 --> 43:18.895
[♪♪♪]

43:23.432 --> 43:24.699
I'll be right back.

43:24.701 --> 43:25.903
Oh, okay.

43:28.271 --> 43:30.207
[PHONE RINGING]

43:32.208 --> 43:34.342
Hey, I just texted you.

43:34.344 --> 43:36.845
I know you sent a text,
but why didn't you call?

43:36.847 --> 43:38.646
I'm in a meeting,
and it's loud,

43:38.648 --> 43:40.184
<i>and I didn't wanna step out.</i>

43:41.384 --> 43:42.818
ANNIE:
Are you at a bar?

43:42.820 --> 43:44.918
<i>Yes,
it's just drinks with clients.</i>

43:44.920 --> 43:46.789
Yeah, but you know
why I'm upset, right?

43:49.659 --> 43:50.958
The text. Yes.

43:50.960 --> 43:52.894
<i>I get it. Um...</i>

43:52.896 --> 43:55.630
Look, it's not like that,
all right?

43:55.632 --> 43:57.798
<i>This is a part of my job.</i>

43:57.800 --> 43:59.967
All right?
It's how we pay for your house.

43:59.969 --> 44:01.036
My house?

44:01.038 --> 44:02.269
<i>[SCOTT GROANS]</i>

44:02.271 --> 44:04.639
<i>Annie, look, let's just not</i>

44:04.641 --> 44:08.108
- get into that again, please.
- <i>You know what? Never mind.</i>

44:08.110 --> 44:10.077
Sorry I bothered you.

44:10.079 --> 44:11.614
[PHONE BEEPS]

44:15.684 --> 44:17.353
[SNIFFLES]

44:19.356 --> 44:20.958
[ANNIE SIGHS]

44:23.927 --> 44:26.059
- Everything okay?
- Yeah.

44:26.061 --> 44:27.931
Yeah.
Scott's just gonna be late.

44:29.798 --> 44:31.134
Trouble at home?

44:37.239 --> 44:38.341
You've got the look.

44:41.010 --> 44:43.177
I really,
really should get home.

44:43.179 --> 44:44.380
Hm.

44:46.615 --> 44:48.450
Uh...

44:48.452 --> 44:49.516
No.

44:49.518 --> 44:50.853
I can't do this.

44:52.989 --> 44:55.956
I need to get my ass
back to Napa.

44:55.958 --> 44:58.194
- I'm sorry.
- That'd be best.

44:59.695 --> 45:01.628
Good night, then.

45:01.630 --> 45:03.863
Good night.

45:03.865 --> 45:06.534
Thank you for being
such a sweetheart, Charlie.

45:06.536 --> 45:07.471
Appreciate it.

45:08.639 --> 45:10.304
Officially, merry Christmas.

45:10.306 --> 45:11.838
Thank you. Merry Christmas.

45:11.840 --> 45:13.173
- See you.
- See you.

45:13.175 --> 45:17.748
<i>♪ All I need ♪</i>

45:19.849 --> 45:23.721
<i>♪ Need ♪</i>

45:26.155 --> 45:29.023
<i>♪ She used to be my baby ♪</i>

45:29.025 --> 45:32.025
<i>♪ But now
I'm in a dark place ♪</i>

45:32.027 --> 45:34.829
<i>♪ And I can't find my way ♪</i>

45:34.831 --> 45:38.166
<i>♪ And every day
I'm waiting... ♪</i>

45:38.168 --> 45:40.168
SCOTT:
Bravo, Annie.

45:40.170 --> 45:41.070
Bravo.

45:43.773 --> 45:44.708
Annie!

45:46.242 --> 45:47.945
House looks fantastic.

45:49.679 --> 45:52.112
How'd you do all that
by yourself?

45:52.114 --> 45:53.082
I didn't.

46:03.760 --> 46:05.195
Wild guess...

46:06.429 --> 46:07.996
Charlie?

46:07.998 --> 46:10.900
We both know you weren't
gonna help me with the lights.

46:13.335 --> 46:15.635
This is about the texting?

46:15.637 --> 46:17.771
You know what's funny?

46:17.773 --> 46:21.075
I'm sitting here,
waiting for you to call,

46:21.077 --> 46:23.911
like you usually do,
and you don't.

46:23.913 --> 46:25.746
- Sitting here with Charlie.
- What?

46:25.748 --> 46:27.382
You're sitting here
with Charlie.

46:27.384 --> 46:29.717
No, we're not doing that.
We're not doing that.

46:29.719 --> 46:31.786
Instead of calling, you text.

46:31.788 --> 46:34.421
- You're worried about a text.
- What happened last time?

46:34.423 --> 46:36.891
It's not okay for me
having drinks with my client,

46:36.893 --> 46:38.126
That's not the point.

46:38.128 --> 46:39.860
It's okay for you
to sit up here

46:39.862 --> 46:42.697
and share wine with the man
that I specifically asked you

46:42.699 --> 46:44.231
not to have in this house.

46:44.233 --> 46:47.168
You text instead of call.
The last time you did that,

46:47.170 --> 46:49.903
- you were with somebody.
- I apologized for that, okay?

46:49.905 --> 46:52.072
Look, we went to therapy.

46:52.074 --> 46:55.342
Then we got married.
Then we bought this house,

46:55.344 --> 46:57.847
and now we're here
to start a family.

46:59.815 --> 47:00.983
Do you trust me?

47:04.253 --> 47:06.454
[SIGHS]

47:06.456 --> 47:07.356
You know what?

47:09.425 --> 47:10.758
Sleep in a different room.

47:10.760 --> 47:12.362
I don't wanna talk about
this shit.

47:20.769 --> 47:21.905
Living the dream.

47:24.206 --> 47:26.509
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

47:29.646 --> 47:31.381
[CREAKING]

47:47.797 --> 47:49.499
[♪♪♪]

48:18.561 --> 48:19.763
[SOFTLY]
Okay.

48:22.998 --> 48:24.266
[SIGHS]

48:24.268 --> 48:26.400
ANNIE:
Honey, what are you doing?

48:26.402 --> 48:28.903
I can hear sounds upstairs.
You scared me.

48:28.905 --> 48:30.338
Okay, come here.
Come here.

48:30.340 --> 48:31.873
- What?
- Hey.

48:31.875 --> 48:33.742
You said you...
You heard sounds?

48:33.744 --> 48:37.211
- Yeah, I heard sounds.
- Do you know what it was?

48:37.213 --> 48:38.348
I thought it was you.

48:39.682 --> 48:41.585
I think I saw him
in the house.

48:42.686 --> 48:44.918
- Who?
- Charlie.

48:44.920 --> 48:46.887
How could he even
get in the house?

48:46.889 --> 48:48.822
You changed the locks.

48:48.824 --> 48:50.724
[♪♪♪]

48:50.726 --> 48:52.495
We have
the security system.

48:54.896 --> 48:56.630
Okay.

48:56.632 --> 48:59.066
I'm tripping. I don't know.

48:59.068 --> 48:59.970
All right.

49:02.572 --> 49:05.273
I think maybe you've been
drinking a little too much.

49:05.275 --> 49:06.773
[SCOFFS]

49:06.775 --> 49:09.712
Look,
I'm sorry for waking you up.

49:10.847 --> 49:12.246
It's okay.

49:12.248 --> 49:14.283
I'm also sorry about earlier.

49:17.353 --> 49:18.387
I'm sorry too.

49:19.588 --> 49:20.489
Come here.

49:50.786 --> 49:52.253
ANNIE:
I love you.

49:52.255 --> 49:54.157
[♪♪♪]

50:15.610 --> 50:16.945
SCOTT:
You look good.

50:16.947 --> 50:17.847
ANNIE:
Thank you.

50:19.581 --> 50:22.851
So, what do you say
we go on a real date tonight?

50:22.853 --> 50:24.385
Dinner?

50:24.387 --> 50:26.820
We'll go to that Italian spot
that we read about.

50:26.822 --> 50:28.021
I'd like that.

50:28.023 --> 50:28.924
All right.

50:31.728 --> 50:33.726
Could I get a medium latte?

50:33.728 --> 50:35.128
- BARISTA 1: Name?
- It's Scott.

50:35.130 --> 50:36.032
Thanks, man.

50:37.300 --> 50:39.133
[CHUCKLES]

50:39.135 --> 50:42.003
I don't mean to stare.
Grady Kramer.

50:42.005 --> 50:43.871
You just bought the Peck house,
right?

50:43.873 --> 50:45.940
- Yeah.
- My wife and I, we live, like,

50:45.942 --> 50:47.374
a mile down the road
from you.

50:47.376 --> 50:48.642
Oh, nice to meet you.

50:48.644 --> 50:49.878
We heard you got a...

50:49.880 --> 50:51.711
A damn good deal
on Charlie's place.

50:51.713 --> 50:54.215
- Well, we did okay.
- Yeah.

50:54.217 --> 50:55.583
Charlie's quite a guy.

50:55.585 --> 50:58.054
Just don't look
too close under the mask.

50:59.054 --> 51:00.022
What do you mean?

51:01.423 --> 51:04.157
You know his wife
died in that house.

51:04.159 --> 51:06.860
Yeah, yeah.
You know, cancer.

51:06.862 --> 51:09.265
Well, maybe she had cancer,
maybe she didn't.

51:10.532 --> 51:12.300
All I know is
that one fine day,

51:12.302 --> 51:15.403
Mrs. Charlie took
Mr. Charlie's shotgun...

51:15.405 --> 51:17.704
[♪♪♪]

51:17.706 --> 51:20.039
<i>...shoved the barrel
in her mouth.</i>

51:20.041 --> 51:21.641
[GUN COCKS]

51:21.643 --> 51:25.781
At least, that's how Charlie
explained it to the police.

51:27.617 --> 51:29.349
- BARISTA 2: Grady.
- Ah.

51:29.351 --> 51:30.920
BARISTA 1:
Medium latte for Scott.

51:32.688 --> 51:34.387
ANNIE:
I don't know.

51:34.389 --> 51:36.690
You think that's blood?

51:36.692 --> 51:38.458
Yeah.

51:38.460 --> 51:42.396
Honey, when did you become
a detective?

51:42.398 --> 51:44.164
And why are you
trying to scare me?

51:44.166 --> 51:46.700
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.
I'm not trying to scare you.

51:46.702 --> 51:48.269
- It's just...
- Okay.

51:48.271 --> 51:50.737
the details surrounding
Ellen's death are sketchy,

51:50.739 --> 51:53.340
to say the least, so I
looked it up on the Internet,

51:53.342 --> 51:55.608
and the DA was considering
a murder charge.

51:55.610 --> 51:57.077
A murder charge.

51:57.079 --> 51:58.778
But then why
didn't they pursue it?

51:58.780 --> 52:00.683
- Lack of evidence.
- Honey,

52:01.983 --> 52:03.883
this doesn't make him
a murderer.

52:03.885 --> 52:07.086
Okay, well, we don't know
anything about this man,

52:07.088 --> 52:09.557
and I've seen the way
that he looks at you.

52:09.559 --> 52:11.325
Now Charlie is after me?

52:11.327 --> 52:12.592
Since day one.

52:12.594 --> 52:13.726
That's ridiculous.

52:13.728 --> 52:15.461
Oh, my God.
You don't see it?

52:15.463 --> 52:18.231
What does it matter? He's going
to Florida any day now.

52:18.233 --> 52:21.267
Is he? Because his departure
date just keeps moving.

52:21.269 --> 52:23.938
So, what do you
want me to do?

52:23.940 --> 52:26.807
Okay, it's simple.
I want you to tell him...

52:26.809 --> 52:29.177
Tell him that
he's not welcome.

52:29.179 --> 52:32.112
Okay?
And if you can't tell him,

52:32.114 --> 52:34.916
then-then I'll...
I'll tell him myself.

52:34.918 --> 52:36.083
You gonna tell him?

52:36.085 --> 52:37.521
You don't think
I'll tell him?

52:39.789 --> 52:41.291
I think we should
go to dinner.

52:42.925 --> 52:44.127
- We're gonna be late.
- Okay.

52:49.130 --> 52:51.666
That was it.
Yeah, that was it.

52:51.668 --> 52:54.001
Oh, this place
is definitely a keeper.

52:54.003 --> 52:56.338
Good pasta,
good wine.

52:57.940 --> 52:59.606
Honey, you gonna be
able to drive?

52:59.608 --> 53:02.010
Yeah. Not only
can I drive, I...

53:02.012 --> 53:04.845
I was thinking maybe we could
stop for a little nightcap.

53:04.847 --> 53:07.750
Oh, baby,
everything is closed.

53:09.184 --> 53:10.818
SCOTT: What about
The Royal Hotel?

53:10.820 --> 53:12.720
ANNIE: I don't think
that's a good idea.

53:12.722 --> 53:14.956
Come on, let's just take
a little sneak peek.

53:14.958 --> 53:16.356
Honey.

53:16.358 --> 53:18.325
To see what
old Charlie's up to

53:18.327 --> 53:20.126
when he's not
haunting our house.

53:20.128 --> 53:21.295
Honey, yeah,
I don't...

53:21.297 --> 53:22.929
- I don't think... No.
- Yeah.

53:22.931 --> 53:24.164
No...

53:24.166 --> 53:26.068
[ROCK SONG PLAYING SOFTLY]

53:29.005 --> 53:31.972
- Oh, come on, honey, let's go.
- No, no, no.

53:31.974 --> 53:32.876
Scott.

53:34.510 --> 53:36.043
- Annie.
- Hi.

53:36.045 --> 53:37.878
- Hello.
- Charlie.

53:37.880 --> 53:40.347
- What are you doing downtown?
- Hey, man.

53:40.349 --> 53:44.751
We were just, uh... Just
having dinner at Fellini's.

53:44.753 --> 53:47.354
I'll buy you a drink.
Annie, what are you having?

53:47.356 --> 53:49.055
I'm good.
I'm actually gonna drive.

53:49.057 --> 53:51.858
Oh, well, Scott,
pick your poison.

53:51.860 --> 53:53.695
- Tequila shot.
- You know what?

53:53.697 --> 53:56.063
But we're not gonna stay late,
Scott has work in the morning.

53:56.065 --> 53:57.831
It's okay.

53:57.833 --> 53:59.368
[COUGHS]

54:00.402 --> 54:02.570
Ah.

54:02.572 --> 54:05.474
- What were we drinking to?
- How about Florida?

54:07.842 --> 54:09.075
When are you leaving?

54:09.077 --> 54:10.911
- Scott.
- No, no.

54:10.913 --> 54:14.514
I'm not trying to be rude.
Just... Just remind me of this.

54:14.516 --> 54:17.184
Your, um, daughter...

54:17.186 --> 54:19.753
Your daughter, what part
does she live in, again?

54:19.755 --> 54:21.188
Fort Myers.

54:21.190 --> 54:23.590
Can we get another round?
This time, it's on me.

54:23.592 --> 54:25.693
- [CHUCKLES]
- All right.

54:25.695 --> 54:27.994
I'm... I'm going to pass.
You have mine.

54:27.996 --> 54:31.664
Because tequila has a way
of sneaking up on me.

54:31.666 --> 54:33.569
[LAUGHING]

54:36.938 --> 54:39.072
So do you, Charlie.

54:39.074 --> 54:43.679
So do you. You... You have a way
of sneaking up on me.

54:44.746 --> 54:45.979
How's that?

54:45.981 --> 54:48.749
You looking for a new wife,
Charlie?

54:48.751 --> 54:51.117
Okay, l-let's go, honey.
It's getting late.

54:51.119 --> 54:53.619
I need an answer.

54:53.621 --> 54:56.356
Your question does not deserve
an answer, Scott.

54:56.358 --> 54:59.026
If you wanna talk,
we can do that some other time.

54:59.028 --> 55:00.728
- Perhaps I'll drop by the house?
- No.

55:00.730 --> 55:04.565
God, no. Damn it, no.
See, that's the problem, man.

55:04.567 --> 55:07.635
No, your days
of dropping by are over.

55:07.637 --> 55:10.974
All right. Well,
then someplace less public.

55:12.173 --> 55:15.210
Stay away from my wife,
okay?

55:16.579 --> 55:19.347
She's just too nice
to tell you herself.

55:19.349 --> 55:21.251
So I'm telling you.

55:22.885 --> 55:23.820
<i>Capiche?</i>

55:24.653 --> 55:26.220
[♪♪♪]

55:26.222 --> 55:28.155
You've made your point.
Let's go.

55:28.157 --> 55:29.757
Be careful on the road.

55:29.759 --> 55:31.027
Scott.

55:34.163 --> 55:35.998
So long, Chuck.

55:37.132 --> 55:38.164
Gotta go.

55:38.166 --> 55:39.432
[GROWLS SOFTLY]

55:39.434 --> 55:40.804
SCOTT:
Come on.

55:44.340 --> 55:45.307
[SOFTLY]
I'm sorry.

55:46.442 --> 55:47.644
It's okay.

55:50.112 --> 55:51.648
[CLEARS THROAT]

55:52.648 --> 55:54.550
[♪♪♪]

55:57.853 --> 55:59.789
<i>[VOICES WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY]</i>

56:15.838 --> 56:17.273
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

56:18.742 --> 56:20.374
[RAP MUSIC PLAYING
ON HEADPHONES]

56:20.376 --> 56:22.876
<i>♪ Yeah, it's on me, on me ♪</i>

56:22.878 --> 56:26.046
<i>♪ Like I can't really trust
All the things you tell me ♪</i>

56:26.048 --> 56:29.516
<i>♪ Like I care if you want out
Of trying to help me, yeah ♪</i>

56:29.518 --> 56:32.552
<i>♪ It's on my mind, I feel
My brain swelling, yeah ♪</i>

56:32.554 --> 56:35.222
<i>♪ It's on me, on me ♪</i>

56:35.224 --> 56:37.557
<i>♪ Like I can't really trust
All the things... ♪</i>

56:37.559 --> 56:39.962
[SONG CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY
ON HEADPHONES]

56:43.364 --> 56:44.365
[TIRES SCREECH]

56:44.367 --> 56:45.999
[GRUNTING]

56:46.001 --> 56:47.066
[TIRES SCREECH]

56:47.068 --> 56:48.971
[GROANING]

57:01.150 --> 57:02.518
<i>[HEART MONITOR BEEPING]</i>

57:05.688 --> 57:07.753
DOCTOR: <i>Your husband
has a mild concussion.</i>

57:07.755 --> 57:10.191
We need to make sure he doesn't
have internal injuries.

57:10.193 --> 57:12.025
I can get out of here
tonight, right?

57:12.027 --> 57:13.559
DOCTOR:
Depends on the lab.

57:13.561 --> 57:15.929
Unfortunately, that means
we gotta keep you overnight.

57:15.931 --> 57:17.430
The only problem
with that is,

57:17.432 --> 57:19.099
I gotta go
to work tomorrow, so...

57:19.101 --> 57:20.300
It's protocol.

57:20.302 --> 57:22.403
[INHALES SHARPLY]
All right.

57:22.405 --> 57:25.238
NARRATOR [ON TV]: <i>The lioness
sprints towards her prey,</i>

57:25.240 --> 57:27.409
<i>a zebra just outside
the grasslands...</i>

57:31.280 --> 57:35.849
Why don't you go home
and get some rest?

57:35.851 --> 57:36.985
I'll be fine.

57:38.454 --> 57:40.824
- Honey, I can stay.
- I know, I know.

57:41.956 --> 57:43.759
But I'll be all right.

57:45.594 --> 57:47.594
You just want me
to get out of your bed

57:47.596 --> 57:49.298
so you have more room.

57:51.233 --> 57:53.066
That's not the case.

57:53.068 --> 57:54.269
Mm-hmm.

57:55.938 --> 57:58.738
I'll pick you up in the morning
when they discharge you.

57:58.740 --> 58:00.474
Yeah, I'll call you.

58:00.476 --> 58:01.411
Okay.

58:03.478 --> 58:05.711
- Love you.
- I love you too.

58:05.713 --> 58:08.815
NARRATOR: <i>As for the
zebra, there is no escape.</i>

58:08.817 --> 58:11.452
<i>Powerful jaws
slowly and swiftly</i>

58:11.454 --> 58:14.324
<i>bring imminent death
and darkness.</i>

58:15.757 --> 58:17.460
[♪♪♪]

58:29.905 --> 58:32.505
- [PHONE RINGS]
- What's up, Scott?

58:32.507 --> 58:34.909
SCOTT: <i>Listen to me very
carefully, all right?</i>

58:34.911 --> 58:36.045
I can't prove it...

58:37.780 --> 58:40.581
but I-I got this feeling
that it was Charlie

58:40.583 --> 58:41.780
who ran me off the road.

58:41.782 --> 58:43.282
Why would he do that?

58:43.284 --> 58:44.985
SCOTT:
<i>Because you were right.</i>

58:44.987 --> 58:47.019
<i>He's obsessed with the house,</i>

58:47.021 --> 58:49.724
and now he's obsessed
with Annie.

58:49.726 --> 58:52.659
Well, have you told Annie what
you're telling me right now?

58:52.661 --> 58:55.996
SCOTT: <i>I tried.
I tried, man, but she just won't buy it.</i>

58:55.998 --> 58:58.199
Look, I need you to do me
a favor, all right?

58:58.201 --> 59:00.934
I need you to get Brian in IT
to discreetly

59:00.936 --> 59:05.472
find out everything he can
on Charlie Peck and his family.

59:05.474 --> 59:07.807
I really need to know
who I'm dealing with.

59:07.809 --> 59:10.844
If there's anything to find
on Charlie Peck,

59:10.846 --> 59:12.378
we're gonna find it.

59:12.380 --> 59:14.283
[♪♪♪]

59:28.230 --> 59:30.432
[DOOR SLAMS]

59:34.068 --> 59:35.572
Hello?

59:51.853 --> 59:53.353
[KNOCK ON DOOR,
DOORBELL RINGS]

59:53.355 --> 59:55.257
[♪♪♪]

59:58.894 --> 01:00:00.827
Charlie, you scared
the shit out of me.

01:00:00.829 --> 01:00:02.496
Oh, I'm so sorry.

01:00:02.498 --> 01:00:03.697
I am so sorry.

01:00:03.699 --> 01:00:05.532
I-I heard about Scott,

01:00:05.534 --> 01:00:09.269
and I just wanted to drop by
and-and, uh, give you this.

01:00:09.271 --> 01:00:10.737
I thought
you might be hungry.

01:00:10.739 --> 01:00:11.838
How is he?

01:00:11.840 --> 01:00:13.340
He's okay.

01:00:13.342 --> 01:00:15.108
They're gonna keep him
overnight.

01:00:15.110 --> 01:00:17.043
When I heard
he was in the hospital,

01:00:17.045 --> 01:00:18.746
it made me think of Ellen,

01:00:18.748 --> 01:00:21.715
and when she was
in the hospital with cancer.

01:00:21.717 --> 01:00:24.751
And I'd come home, and the house
would be dark and empty,

01:00:24.753 --> 01:00:26.822
and I was pretty blue...

01:00:28.155 --> 01:00:29.692
and lonely, so...

01:00:31.425 --> 01:00:33.894
Anyway, I got you, uh,
an everything pizza.

01:00:33.896 --> 01:00:36.429
You just pick off
what you don't like.

01:00:36.431 --> 01:00:37.798
- All right?
- Okay.

01:00:37.800 --> 01:00:40.733
And I'm... I'm sorry, uh,
that I scared you.

01:00:40.735 --> 01:00:42.269
It's okay.

01:00:42.271 --> 01:00:44.403
- Uh, good night.
- Good night.

01:00:44.405 --> 01:00:45.340
All right.

01:00:46.742 --> 01:00:48.211
Charlie.

01:00:49.244 --> 01:00:50.677
[CHUCKLES]

01:00:50.679 --> 01:00:52.579
This pizza is huge.

01:00:52.581 --> 01:00:55.014
You're not gonna make me
eat it alone, are you?

01:00:55.016 --> 01:00:58.017
- You want some company?
- Come on in.

01:00:58.019 --> 01:01:01.521
Brian and I found out
that old Charlie boy is

01:01:01.523 --> 01:01:04.291
- in some deep legal shit.
- What?

01:01:04.293 --> 01:01:06.726
Yeah. You know, his
entire construction business,

01:01:06.728 --> 01:01:08.228
it went under.

01:01:08.230 --> 01:01:10.929
There were lawsuits,
government liens,

01:01:10.931 --> 01:01:12.932
charges of tax fraud.

01:01:12.934 --> 01:01:16.635
I mean, this guy was looking
at some serious jail time.

01:01:16.637 --> 01:01:19.139
Yeah, he didn't wanna sell it.
He had to.

01:01:19.141 --> 01:01:21.811
And he owed everybody.

01:01:23.112 --> 01:01:25.179
- What have I done?
- I'm sorry, man.

01:01:25.181 --> 01:01:27.113
<i>He's not
the upstanding citizen</i>

01:01:27.115 --> 01:01:29.016
<i>that he wants us
to think he is.</i>

01:01:29.018 --> 01:01:33.153
Not exactly your traditional
holiday meal, is it?

01:01:33.155 --> 01:01:36.822
No, but I'm starving,
so this is perfect.

01:01:36.824 --> 01:01:38.624
SCOTT: <i>On your way
back to the city,</i>

01:01:38.626 --> 01:01:41.293
just go by the house
and check on Annie for me, okay?

01:01:41.295 --> 01:01:43.262
Make sure she's all right,
call me back.

01:01:43.264 --> 01:01:45.197
- MIKE: <i>Of course, of course.</i>
- SCOTT: <i>Cool?</i>

01:01:45.199 --> 01:01:46.833
MIKE:
<i>Yeah, I got you.</i>

01:01:46.835 --> 01:01:48.434
[ENGINE REVS]

01:01:48.436 --> 01:01:50.537
You know those guys
that wear yellow vests?

01:01:50.539 --> 01:01:52.706
- Oh, yeah.
- You know, that stop traffic?

01:01:52.708 --> 01:01:54.474
- I was... That was me.
- Mm.

01:01:54.476 --> 01:01:56.175
- CHARLIE: <i>And... Yeah.</i>
- ANNIE: <i>No.</i>

01:01:56.177 --> 01:01:57.978
CHARLIE:
<i>And it just so happened</i>

01:01:57.980 --> 01:02:00.246
that I turned my stop sign
around for traffic,

01:02:00.248 --> 01:02:02.749
and she was
the first car in line.

01:02:02.751 --> 01:02:04.150
<i>And she was so...</i>

01:02:04.152 --> 01:02:05.786
[♪♪♪]

01:02:05.788 --> 01:02:07.856
MIKE: What the hell
is Charlie doing here?

01:02:14.329 --> 01:02:16.099
[LAUGHING]
And she had said...

01:02:18.132 --> 01:02:21.367
She had told me that,
"I have to be somewhere,"

01:02:21.369 --> 01:02:23.205
and I came over
to her window...

01:02:25.541 --> 01:02:29.242
After 15 minutes of talking
to her, I had a date with her.

01:02:29.244 --> 01:02:31.610
- [CHUCKLES]
- That's so sweet.

01:02:31.612 --> 01:02:34.951
CHARLIE: Yeah, from there we
just, like I said...

01:02:36.552 --> 01:02:38.485
- This is great wine, isn't it?
- It's good.

01:02:38.487 --> 01:02:39.885
Would you like
another glass?

01:02:39.887 --> 01:02:41.090
Yeah, that'd be great.

01:03:02.744 --> 01:03:04.577
So...

01:03:04.579 --> 01:03:07.713
Annie. Don't look over
your shoulder, all right?

01:03:07.715 --> 01:03:09.618
But there's someone
watching us...

01:03:10.952 --> 01:03:12.619
from outside
the kitchen window.

01:03:12.621 --> 01:03:14.420
- Should I call the cops?
- No.

01:03:14.422 --> 01:03:16.523
I'm sure it's those
high school kids,

01:03:16.525 --> 01:03:19.693
- but I'm fed up.
- Okay.

01:03:19.695 --> 01:03:21.028
I'm gonna go check it out.

01:03:21.030 --> 01:03:22.265
- All right.
- All right.

01:03:30.172 --> 01:03:31.505
CHARLIE:
Hey!

01:03:31.507 --> 01:03:33.442
[♪♪♪]

01:03:42.451 --> 01:03:44.353
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

01:03:46.422 --> 01:03:48.324
[♪♪♪]

01:03:50.726 --> 01:03:51.958
[SHOUTS]

01:03:51.960 --> 01:03:53.461
Mike?

01:03:54.463 --> 01:03:55.829
Charlie.

01:03:55.831 --> 01:03:58.130
- What are you doing out here?
- I can explain.

01:03:58.132 --> 01:04:00.633
If I'd had a gun, I could
have blown your head off.

01:04:00.635 --> 01:04:01.834
I know, man.

01:04:01.836 --> 01:04:03.637
Right now
I feel like a damn fool.

01:04:03.639 --> 01:04:05.208
What did you
expect to see?

01:04:06.307 --> 01:04:08.273
- I don't know.
- Mike.

01:04:08.275 --> 01:04:10.110
- Mike...
- [AX SCRAPES]

01:04:10.112 --> 01:04:12.278
This is not the suburbs.

01:04:12.280 --> 01:04:13.847
This is the country.

01:04:13.849 --> 01:04:16.016
People have guns.
You've got to be careful.

01:04:16.018 --> 01:04:17.650
[SIGHS]

01:04:17.652 --> 01:04:19.751
I know, man.
I do not belong here.

01:04:19.753 --> 01:04:21.755
Where's your car?

01:04:21.757 --> 01:04:24.023
I just parked at
the end of the driveway.

01:04:24.025 --> 01:04:25.358
I'll walk you to it.

01:04:25.360 --> 01:04:27.494
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:04:27.496 --> 01:04:30.530
- You scared me to death.
- Yeah, I know. You scared me.

01:04:30.532 --> 01:04:32.633
You're shaking
like a leaf.

01:04:32.635 --> 01:04:34.133
[LAUGHS]

01:04:34.135 --> 01:04:36.336
You wanna have a cigarette,
calm your nerves?

01:04:36.338 --> 01:04:38.871
- No, man. I'm good.
- Go ahead, have a cigarette.

01:04:38.873 --> 01:04:41.476
- No, no, I'll just go...
- No, no, no. I insist.

01:04:43.112 --> 01:04:44.579
Have a cigarette.

01:04:45.447 --> 01:04:47.349
[♪♪♪]

01:04:54.322 --> 01:04:55.891
May I have one?

01:04:59.494 --> 01:05:00.693
I thought you quit.

01:05:00.695 --> 01:05:03.865
[CHUCKLES]
Yeah. Right.

01:05:09.403 --> 01:05:10.806
Thank you.

01:05:16.744 --> 01:05:18.179
Here, let me help you.

01:05:31.527 --> 01:05:33.829
I'm gonna save mine
for later.

01:05:37.965 --> 01:05:38.900
Okay.

01:05:47.742 --> 01:05:50.744
- Think I'm just gonna go.
- All right. Hey.

01:05:50.746 --> 01:05:52.512
Do you believe
in second chances?

01:05:52.514 --> 01:05:55.213
Yeah, sure. I think everybody
deserves a second chance,

01:05:55.215 --> 01:05:56.916
even Peeping Toms.

01:05:56.918 --> 01:06:00.554
No, I'm not talking about that.
I'm talking about in life.

01:06:00.556 --> 01:06:04.090
Like, if you lost everything
that was important to you,

01:06:04.092 --> 01:06:06.892
and then you had a chance
to get it all back,

01:06:06.894 --> 01:06:08.494
wouldn't you just go for it?

01:06:08.496 --> 01:06:09.896
- Hell, yeah.
- Yeah.

01:06:09.898 --> 01:06:11.465
Well, that's like me.

01:06:11.467 --> 01:06:14.400
I have a chance
to get it all back.

01:06:14.402 --> 01:06:15.869
All I have to do

01:06:15.871 --> 01:06:18.037
is just get rid of Scott.

01:06:18.039 --> 01:06:19.472
What the...?

01:06:19.474 --> 01:06:21.307
- [GROANS]
- [HEART MONITOR BEEPS]

01:06:21.309 --> 01:06:22.344
[PANTING]

01:06:24.313 --> 01:06:26.248
[GROANING]

01:06:34.990 --> 01:06:37.193
All right.
Where am I gonna put you?

01:06:38.760 --> 01:06:40.663
[♪♪♪]

01:06:45.768 --> 01:06:47.670
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:06:51.106 --> 01:06:53.773
[INHALES AND EXHALES
SHARPLY]

01:06:53.775 --> 01:06:55.608
[WINCES]

01:06:55.610 --> 01:06:57.145
[GRUNTS]

01:07:05.454 --> 01:07:07.854
- Hi.
- Are you okay?

01:07:07.856 --> 01:07:10.456
Oh, I-I twisted
my damn ankle.

01:07:10.458 --> 01:07:11.992
Oh, my God.

01:07:11.994 --> 01:07:13.659
Okay, just...
There we go.

01:07:13.661 --> 01:07:15.561
I think
I just hit something.

01:07:15.563 --> 01:07:17.030
Idiot. I was...

01:07:17.032 --> 01:07:18.498
Oh, let's put this up.

01:07:18.500 --> 01:07:20.099
I was chasing
those kids.

01:07:20.101 --> 01:07:22.836
Then I hooked my foot
into a tree root.

01:07:22.838 --> 01:07:24.838
I'm gonna, um,
take your boot off

01:07:24.840 --> 01:07:27.307
- and just see if...
- Yeah.

01:07:27.309 --> 01:07:29.842
- Here we go. Okay.
- Ah, all right.

01:07:29.844 --> 01:07:31.778
- Right here. Just...
- Ow!

01:07:31.780 --> 01:07:33.345
- Is it okay? Did that hurt?
- Yeah.

01:07:33.347 --> 01:07:35.414
It's all right.
Yeah, it's all right.

01:07:35.416 --> 01:07:37.018
Okay,
I'm just gonna see if...

01:07:38.219 --> 01:07:40.320
I mean, it doesn't...

01:07:40.322 --> 01:07:43.655
Doesn't seem like
it's swollen or anything.

01:07:43.657 --> 01:07:47.327
You might just have to rest it
when you get to the hotel.

01:07:47.329 --> 01:07:48.728
Yeah.

01:07:48.730 --> 01:07:52.499
You definitely didn't break it.
Thank goodness.

01:07:52.501 --> 01:07:54.501
Yeah, I think
if you prop it up,

01:07:54.503 --> 01:07:56.903
maybe elevate it,
you know, then it'll...

01:07:56.905 --> 01:07:58.704
Hopefully
it'll be okay.

01:07:58.706 --> 01:08:02.277
Feel like you might need to just
double-check and see a doctor.

01:08:03.777 --> 01:08:05.744
You know...

01:08:05.746 --> 01:08:09.749
those kids might come back.
You think maybe I should stay?

01:08:09.751 --> 01:08:12.385
[♪♪♪]

01:08:12.387 --> 01:08:15.121
No, I think,
you know, it's kids.

01:08:15.123 --> 01:08:17.558
I don't think I'm in any real
danger or anything.

01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:18.657
Do you?

01:08:18.658 --> 01:08:19.992
No.

01:08:19.993 --> 01:08:22.062
I don't.

01:08:22.064 --> 01:08:23.765
And I need
to get cleaned up.

01:08:24.867 --> 01:08:26.433
- Yeah.
- I'm dirty.

01:08:26.435 --> 01:08:28.433
I'm so sorry.

01:08:28.435 --> 01:08:30.736
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

01:08:30.738 --> 01:08:32.671
Could you just give me
my boot, please?

01:08:32.673 --> 01:08:34.441
Yeah, let me help you.

01:08:34.443 --> 01:08:36.041
- You got it? Here.
- Yeah, I have...

01:08:36.042 --> 01:08:37.743
I have things to do
in the morning.

01:08:37.746 --> 01:08:39.078
Let me put it
here for you.

01:08:39.081 --> 01:08:39.981
Anyway.

01:08:41.948 --> 01:08:43.415
- You got it?
- Yeah.

01:08:43.417 --> 01:08:44.718
- You help me up?
- Help up?

01:08:44.720 --> 01:08:46.285
- Sure.
- Yeah.

01:08:46.287 --> 01:08:47.754
Here we go.

01:08:47.756 --> 01:08:49.656
- [GRUNTS]
- Okay. Okay.

01:08:49.658 --> 01:08:51.991
Here, let me.
There we go, there we go.

01:08:51.993 --> 01:08:55.495
Okay, here. Come around slowly.
Just push... There we go.

01:08:55.497 --> 01:08:57.263
[♪♪♪]

01:08:57.265 --> 01:08:59.167
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:09:15.885 --> 01:09:17.786
<i>[SHOWER FAUCET RUNNING]</i>

01:09:18.953 --> 01:09:20.622
[DOOR CREAKS]

01:09:22.591 --> 01:09:24.493
[♪♪♪]

01:10:02.230 --> 01:10:04.229
- [CELL PHONE RINGING]
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]

01:10:04.231 --> 01:10:05.897
[♪♪♪]

01:10:05.899 --> 01:10:07.835
[LINE OUT RINGING]

01:10:09.104 --> 01:10:11.303
[DOOR SHUTS]

01:10:11.305 --> 01:10:14.840
ANNIE [ON RECORDING]: <i>Hi.
You've reached Annie. Leave a message.</i>

01:10:14.842 --> 01:10:16.744
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

01:10:24.552 --> 01:10:26.488
[♪♪♪]

01:11:03.390 --> 01:11:04.456
CHARLIE:
Hey.

01:11:04.458 --> 01:11:06.394
[♪♪♪]

01:11:08.262 --> 01:11:09.998
How you feeling?

01:11:24.378 --> 01:11:27.246
You're bringing my wife
flowers now?

01:11:27.248 --> 01:11:28.483
It's foxglove.

01:11:29.850 --> 01:11:32.218
I haven't seen it
around here

01:11:32.220 --> 01:11:34.323
in a long, long,
long time.

01:11:36.591 --> 01:11:38.058
You okay?

01:11:38.060 --> 01:11:39.495
Look, I know about you.

01:11:41.429 --> 01:11:43.431
Your losses,
your bankruptcy,

01:11:44.565 --> 01:11:46.135
why you sold us the house.

01:11:48.235 --> 01:11:49.137
So...

01:11:50.505 --> 01:11:52.875
get the fuck off
of my property.

01:11:54.242 --> 01:11:56.145
[♪♪♪]

01:12:20.435 --> 01:12:22.338
[WHISTLING]

01:12:31.113 --> 01:12:32.911
SCOTT:
Annie.

01:12:32.913 --> 01:12:35.550
Babe, I would have came
and got you. You okay?

01:12:40.154 --> 01:12:41.286
What's wrong?

01:12:41.288 --> 01:12:43.123
I just ran into Charlie.

01:12:43.125 --> 01:12:44.557
He was bringing you flowers.

01:12:44.559 --> 01:12:46.125
Nobody knocked on the door.

01:12:46.127 --> 01:12:47.660
Did he come by here
last night?

01:12:47.662 --> 01:12:49.794
He came by
to see if I was okay.

01:12:49.796 --> 01:12:52.701
I think he's the one that tried
to run me off the road.

01:12:54.368 --> 01:12:56.835
You think Charlie tried
to run you off the road?

01:12:56.837 --> 01:12:58.838
Yes.

01:12:58.840 --> 01:13:00.943
Look, he's not
who you think he is.

01:13:04.712 --> 01:13:06.646
What time did Mike
leave last night?

01:13:06.648 --> 01:13:08.046
- Mike?
- Yeah.

01:13:08.048 --> 01:13:09.848
Mike didn't come by
here last night.

01:13:09.850 --> 01:13:12.085
No, no, no. I sent Mike
to come check on you.

01:13:12.087 --> 01:13:14.254
Mike left straight
from the hospital to come

01:13:14.256 --> 01:13:16.289
- check on you.
- Honey, he didn't come here.

01:13:16.291 --> 01:13:17.990
So you were here alone
last night

01:13:17.992 --> 01:13:19.224
by yourself with Charlie?

01:13:19.226 --> 01:13:21.059
- He came by to see if I was okay.
- Why?

01:13:21.061 --> 01:13:22.896
He knew you weren't here.
He brought some food.

01:13:22.898 --> 01:13:24.630
There was somebody
in the backyard.

01:13:24.632 --> 01:13:26.031
It turned out to
be the kids.

01:13:26.033 --> 01:13:27.500
I called you
a bunch of times.

01:13:27.502 --> 01:13:29.735
- Listen to what you just said.
- I sent him home.

01:13:29.737 --> 01:13:32.074
How did he know?
How did he know I wasn't here?

01:13:33.375 --> 01:13:35.808
Think about that.
How did he know?

01:13:35.810 --> 01:13:37.977
[♪♪♪]

01:13:37.979 --> 01:13:40.246
This... This guy
is dangerous. Okay?

01:13:40.248 --> 01:13:41.848
Charlie is
very dangerous.

01:13:41.850 --> 01:13:44.286
Okay. Okay, babe,
I believe you. I do.

01:13:46.421 --> 01:13:49.554
He shows up again,
you just...

01:13:49.556 --> 01:13:51.723
Just call the police,
okay?

01:13:51.725 --> 01:13:53.425
- Just call them.
- Okay.

01:13:53.427 --> 01:13:55.562
[LINE OUT RINGING]

01:13:55.564 --> 01:13:57.062
WOMAN [ON PHONE]:
<i>Napa Police.</i>

01:13:57.064 --> 01:13:59.098
Hi. I'd like to get
a restraining order.

01:13:59.100 --> 01:14:01.003
[♪♪♪]

01:14:04.738 --> 01:14:06.371
[LINE OUT RINGING]

01:14:06.373 --> 01:14:08.607
MIKE [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Hey, this is Mike Renfro.</i>

01:14:08.609 --> 01:14:10.612
<i>Leave your name and number
after the beep.</i>

01:14:15.283 --> 01:14:17.517
- [CELL PHONE RINGING]
- SCOTT: Hello?

01:14:17.519 --> 01:14:19.718
WOMAN: <i>Yes,
I'm calling for Mr. Scott Howard.</i>

01:14:19.720 --> 01:14:21.420
This is he.

01:14:21.422 --> 01:14:23.423
WOMAN: <i>Mr. Howard,
I'm curious if you have</i>

01:14:23.425 --> 01:14:25.258
<i>an alternate address
for Mr. Peck</i>

01:14:25.260 --> 01:14:28.394
<i>because we've not yet been able
to serve the restraining order.</i>

01:14:28.396 --> 01:14:30.362
- What?
- <i>He's not at The Royal Hotel.</i>

01:14:30.364 --> 01:14:33.366
What are you talking about?
Can you double-check, please?

01:14:33.368 --> 01:14:35.968
<i>I'm sorry, sir. We've gone
through all their records,</i>

01:14:35.970 --> 01:14:38.638
<i>and Mr. Peck has never stayed
at The Royal Hotel.</i>

01:14:38.640 --> 01:14:40.309
[♪♪♪]

01:14:41.309 --> 01:14:42.709
- Brian.
- Hey, Scott.

01:14:42.711 --> 01:14:45.144
Tell me, did you
hear back from Mike?

01:14:45.146 --> 01:14:47.213
No one's seen or heard
from Mike.

01:14:47.215 --> 01:14:49.415
What about Charlie Peck,
his kids?

01:14:49.417 --> 01:14:51.785
Did you...? Did you find
anything about his kids?

01:14:51.787 --> 01:14:53.285
I did a lot of digging.

01:14:53.287 --> 01:14:54.853
There's not much there,

01:14:54.855 --> 01:14:57.956
but I did manage to find
a work cell for a Vanessa Smith.

01:14:57.958 --> 01:15:00.326
His daughter's name is Cassidy.
I told you this.

01:15:00.328 --> 01:15:02.831
It was. She changed it
two years ago.

01:15:04.832 --> 01:15:05.964
Wait.

01:15:05.966 --> 01:15:07.267
CHARLIE:
<i>Ellen.</i>

01:15:07.269 --> 01:15:10.035
I lost her to cancer
two years ago.

01:15:10.037 --> 01:15:12.670
- Two years ago?
- Yeah.

01:15:12.672 --> 01:15:15.473
Text me the cell, all right?
I'll call her from the car.

01:15:15.475 --> 01:15:17.578
Sure. Hey, let me know
if you hear from Mike.

01:15:19.980 --> 01:15:22.415
- WOMAN [ON PHONE]: <i>Hello?</i>
- SCOTT: Hello. Have I...?

01:15:22.417 --> 01:15:23.719
Have I reached Cassidy Peck?

01:15:27.488 --> 01:15:30.123
- Who is this?
- SCOTT: <i>My name is Scott Howard,</i>

01:15:30.125 --> 01:15:32.924
and my wife and I bought
the house that you grew up in.

01:15:32.926 --> 01:15:36.129
I'm calling in regards
to your father, Charles Peck.

01:15:36.131 --> 01:15:37.662
[PHONE BEEPS]

